{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/42840097/nhtsa-opens-probe-into-26-million-tesla-vehicles-after-complaint-of-crash-involving-actually-smart-summon-feature", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-07T12:00:02", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-07", "summary": "The NHTSA opened an investigation into approximately 2.6 million Tesla vehicles regarding the 'Actually Smart Summon' feature following crash reports where vehicles failed to detect posts or parked cars. This is the second NHTSA probe into Tesla in under six months, following an October investigation into 2.4 million vehicles involving FSD in reduced visibility conditions. Tesla rolled out the 'Actually Smart Summon' feature in the U.S. in early September and in China in December.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1114, "out": 105}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/42839105/tesla-reminisces-delivering-first-model-3-from-giga-shanghai-after-marking-delivery-growth-in-china-in-2024", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-07T11:11:10", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-07", "summary": "Tesla celebrated the five-year anniversary of delivering the first Model 3 from its Giga Shanghai factory, which has since produced over 3 million vehicles. The facility has an annual capacity exceeding 950,000 vehicles. In 2024, Tesla sold approximately 657,000 vehicles in China, an 8.8% year-on-year increase, despite a global delivery decline to 1.79 million vehicles. The company is also preparing to start mass production of energy storage products at a new Chinese factory in Q1 2025.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 782, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/global/25/01/42838053/us-adds-tencent-tesla-supplier-catl-to-chinese-military-blacklist-shares-tumble", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-07T09:38:23", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-07", "summary": "The U.S. Department of Defense added Tesla supplier CATL and Tencent to its 'Section 1260H' blacklist, alleging support for China's military. Following the news, CATL shares fell 6% in Shenzhen and Tencent shares dropped 7.8% in Hong Kong. Both companies denied the allegations. This action occurs amid escalating trade tensions, including China's recent imposition of trade controls on 28 U.S. companies and the placement of major U.S. defense contractors on its Unreliable Entity List.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 782, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/42837223/teslas-foundation-series-cybertruck-inventory-still-haunts-elon-musk-led-ev-giant-despite-offers", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-07T07:51:28", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-07", "summary": "Tesla continues to hold inventory of 'Foundation Series' Cybertrucks in the U.S., priced at $99,990. Despite offering incentives such as free supercharging for orders placed on or after December 27, the vehicles remain unsold. Tesla began selling a regular version of the Cybertruck in October, priced approximately $20,000 lower than the Foundation Series, suggesting limited consumer demand for the premium-priced initial edition.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 782, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/01/42836706/tesla-supplier-panasonic-energy-targets-reduced-reliance-on-china-for-us-battery-supplies-says-it-is-no1-objective", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-07T06:46:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-07", "summary": "Panasonic Energy, a key Tesla battery supplier, has made reducing reliance on China its 'No. 1 objective' in response to potential U.S. tariff increases. The company operates a plant in Nevada and plans to open a Kansas facility this year. While BYD surpassed Tesla as the world's largest battery electric vehicle seller in Q4 2024, Tesla remains the top-selling pure EV brand for the year, with 83,000 units sold in China in December alone.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 782, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/42836119/gary-blacks-fund-moves-tesla-to-3rd-largest-holding-behind-nvidia-and-alphabet-despite-delivery-miss", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-07T04:44:34", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-07", "summary": "Tesla is now the third-largest holding at The Future Fund LLC, behind Nvidia and Alphabet. Managing partner Gary Black maintains a $380 price target for Tesla, citing a potential $25,000-$30,000 vehicle launch in early 2025 as a catalyst. However, he noted risks regarding the potential elimination of the $7,500 EV tax credit. Tesla reported 495,570 deliveries in Q4, missing analyst expectations of 506,763 and marking the company's first annual sales decline.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 782, "out": 121}}
