{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/01/42922091/spacex-apple-airbnb-and-more-companies-pitch-in-to-support-california-residents-after-wildfires-we-want-to-help", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T17:52:08", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-11", "summary": "Tesla is supporting California residents affected by wildfires by forgiving Autopilot and FSD Supervised strikes to assist with evacuation efforts. Other companies, including SpaceX, Apple, Airbnb, and Lyft, are also providing relief through services like free Starlink terminals, payment postponements, and temporary housing.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1025, "out": 115}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/news/25/01/42915472/in-depth-analysis-tesla-versus-competitors-in-automobiles-industry", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T15:00:40", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "A comparative analysis of Tesla against industry peers shows it has a P/E ratio of 108.20, P/B of 18.13, and P/S of 14.19, all significantly higher than industry averages. While Tesla shows a 3.18% ROE and 7.85% revenue growth, its EBITDA of $4.22 billion and gross profit of $5.0 billion are lower than the industry average. Tesla maintains a debt-to-equity ratio of 0.18.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1025, "out": 115}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/global/25/01/42910173/palantir-co-founder-joe-lonsdale-sets-realistic-expectations-for-elon-musks-doge-initiative-next-trillion-will-be-a-lot-harder", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T12:51:51", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "Palantir co-founder Joe Lonsdale stated that while $1 trillion in federal spending cuts via the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) is achievable, further reductions will be difficult due to bureaucratic and political resistance. The initiative, led by Tesla CEO Elon Musk, initially targeted $2 trillion in cuts. Lonsdale identified fraud reduction, entitlement reform, and unused government buildings as potential savings areas but expressed skepticism regarding defense spending cuts.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/42909595/tesla-recalls-over-239000-vehicles-over-rearview-camera-image-display-issues", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T12:19:27", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "Tesla is recalling 239,382 vehicles in the U.S. (2024-25 Model 3 and Model S; 2023-25 Model X and Model Y) due to a potential computer circuit board short that can cause a loss of the rearview camera image. Tesla is providing an over-the-air software update and will replace affected computers at no cost. The company reports no known collisions or injuries related to this issue. Tesla shares closed at $394.94 on Thursday, with a consensus neutral rating and a $293.23 price target.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/42907586/tesla-model-3-prices-rise-in-china-as-refreshed-model-y-debuts", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T10:52:40", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "Tesla increased the price of all Model 3 variants in China by 3,600 yuan (approx. $491). The base model now starts at 235,500 yuan, the Long Range AWD at 275,500 yuan, and the Performance at 339,500 yuan. Additionally, Tesla launched a refreshed Model Y in China starting at 263,500 yuan, which is 5.4% higher than the previous version. In 2024, Tesla sold approximately 657,000 vehicles in China, an 8.8% year-on-year increase, despite a global delivery decline to 1.79 million vehicles.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/42906316/tesla-says-fsd-strikeouts-will-be-forgiven-in-california-to-help-evacuation-efforts-amidst-wildfires", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T08:46:43", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "Tesla announced it will forgive all Autopilot and Full Self-Driving (FSD) 'strikeouts' for drivers in California to assist with evacuations during the Los Angeles area wildfires. A strikeout occurs when the system disengages due to driver inattentiveness; five strikeouts result in a one-week suspension. SpaceX is also supporting relief efforts by providing free Starlink kits and one month of free service to impacted areas.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/42905406/tesla-launches-refreshed-model-y-in-china-amid-rising-competition", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T06:46:10", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "Tesla launched a refreshed Model Y in China featuring a new design, higher quality interior, and longer range. The launch series starts at 263,500 yuan for the rear-wheel drive and 303,500 yuan for the long-range all-wheel drive, representing a 5.4% price increase over the previous version. Deliveries are expected to begin in March, pending regulatory approval. The Performance variant is not currently listed.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/01/42904409/elon-musk-hosts-x-spaces-with-afds-alice-weidel-after-successfully-endorsing-trump-share-views-on-nuclear-power-and-future-of-europe-with-far-right-german-leader", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T02:09:27", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "Elon Musk hosted a 75-minute discussion on X with Alice Weidel, co-leader of Germany's AfD party, expressing support for the party and criticizing Germany's decision to shut down nuclear power plants. The conversation covered energy policy, immigration, and the war in Ukraine. Tesla's Gigafactory Berlin-Brandenburg, which produced over 400,000 Model Y vehicles by November 2024, remains a critical asset in the region.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/42904377/tesla-bull-gary-black-warns-against-inflated-optimus-robot-assumptions-get-pounded-each-time-i-try-to-right-size-expectations", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-10T02:00:41", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-10", "summary": "Investor Gary Black cautioned against unrealistic expectations for Tesla's Optimus robot, estimating that producing 500,000 units by 2027 would add $0.70 to EPS. Musk has stated goals of producing several thousand units in 2025, scaling to 50,000-100,000 in 2026, and 500,000 in 2027. Bank of America analyst John Murphy valued the Optimus segment at $14 billion to $95 billion, noting that robotaxi and FSD capabilities represent over 75% of Tesla's future value.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/42931833/hewlett-packard-enterprise-strikes-1b-ai-server-deal-with-elon-musks-x-report", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-11T07:41:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-11", "summary": "Hewlett Packard Enterprise secured a deal worth over $1 billion to supply AI-optimized servers to Elon Musk's platform, X. The deal was finalized late last year, beating out competitors Dell and Super Micro Computer. Musk also announced that his xAI startup's Grok chatbot will soon be integrated into Tesla vehicles, allowing users to interact with their cars via voice.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 749, "out": 131}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/health-care/25/01/42935746/is-elon-musks-mental-health-a-cause-for-concern-biographer-thinks-so", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-12T21:00:32", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-13", "summary": "Biographer Seth Abramson has expressed concerns regarding Elon Musk's mental health, citing Musk's own admissions of drug use, stress, and mental illness. Abramson, who has tracked Musk for two years, argues that Musk's erratic behavior and upcoming role as head of the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) pose risks to national stability and civilization-essential industries.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1124, "out": 109}}
