{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/social-media/25/01/42965533/elon-musk-emerges-as-potential-tiktok-us-buyer-as-ban-deadline-looms-company-terms-it-pure-fiction", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-14T02:46:11", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-14", "summary": "Reports suggest Chinese officials are considering Tesla CEO Elon Musk as a potential buyer for TikTok's U.S. operations, which face a January 19 divestment deadline. The deal is estimated at $40 billion to $50 billion, though a TikTok spokesperson dismissed the report as 'pure fiction'.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 786, "out": 89}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/42965139/tesla-soars-over-2-after-hours-on-morgan-stanleys-430-target-upgrade-and-breakthrough-fsd-advancements-says-gary-black", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-14T01:48:07", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-14", "summary": "Tesla shares rose over 2% after-hours following Morgan Stanley raising its price target to $430 from $400, with a bull case of $800. Gary Black noted positive feedback on the refreshed Model Y and FSD v13.2, which reportedly showed a 750% efficacy increase to 724 miles per disengagement. Despite the rejection of Elon Musk's $56 billion pay package and the exit of Stichting Pensioenfonds ABP in Q3 2024, the stock is up 83.40% over the past year.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1217, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/42938578/jamie-dimon-calls-elon-musk-an-extraordinary-talent-jp-morgan-ceo-shares-why-trumps-election-victory-didnt-surprise-him", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-13T08:57:50", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-13", "summary": "JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon praised Tesla CEO Elon Musk as an 'extraordinary talent' for his work at Tesla and SpaceX. Dimon dismissed concerns regarding Musk's political influence and expressed 'cautious pessimism' about the economy. Dimon also noted that Donald Trump's 2024 election victory was not a surprise, attributing it to public frustration with government inefficiency.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1217, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43014719/whats-going-on-with-tesla-shares-wednesday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T20:55:20", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Tesla stock rose 8.04% to $428.08 on Wednesday. Kelley Blue Book ranked the Model Y and Model 3 as the top two best-selling EVs in 2024, though Tesla's total sales volume decreased by approximately 37,000 units compared to 2023 due to increased competition. The Cybertruck ranked fifth on the list. Cox Automotive forecasts EV market share to reach 10% or more in 2025.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1217, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/economics/macro-economic-events/25/01/43011444/wall-street-rallies-as-treasury-yields-fall-banks-smash-q4-earnings-oil-hits-80-whats-driving-markets-wednesday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T17:53:19", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Wall Street rallied on Wednesday as December CPI rose 2.9% year-over-year, fueling expectations for Fed rate cuts in 2025. Financial stocks led the gains following strong Q4 earnings from firms like JPMorgan and Goldman Sachs. Tesla shares climbed over 5% after RBC increased its price target from $313 to $440 and reaffirmed an outperform rating.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1217, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/options/25/01/43011109/8-consumer-discretionary-stocks-whale-activity-in-todays-session", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T17:35:20", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Options activity for Tesla on January 15, 2025, showed a bullish call sweep expiring January 17, 2025, with 189 contracts at a $420 strike price. The total trade price was $170.1K, involving 66,013 contracts traded today against 20,804 in prior open interest.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1217, "out": 119}}
