{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/media/25/01/42997916/tesla-to-suspend-parts-of-refreshed-model-y-lines-in-shanghai-for-3-weeks-report", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T11:59:58", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-15", "summary": "Tesla plans to suspend parts of its Shanghai manufacturing lines for the refreshed Model Y from Jan. 22 to Feb. 14 to prepare for increased production. The Model 3 line will also be closed from Jan. 26 to Feb. 3. The refreshed Model Y, launched in China last week, starts at 263,500 yuan, a 5.4% increase over the previous version, with deliveries expected in March. Tesla reported 1.79 million global deliveries in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023, while BYD delivered over 1.76 million BEVs.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/42995131/10-best-selling-evs-in-us-in-2024", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T08:03:09", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-15", "summary": "Over 1.3 million EVs were sold in the U.S. in 2024, a 7.3% year-on-year increase. Tesla led with the Model Y (372,613 units, 28.6% market share) and Model 3 (189,903 units, 14.6% share). Ford's Mustang Mach-E (51,745 units) and F-150 Lightning (33,510 units) ranked 3rd and 6th. Hyundai's Ioniq 5 sold 44,400 units, while Tesla's Cybertruck sold 38,965 units. Honda's Prologue sold 33,017 units. Cox Automotive expects 2025 to be a record year for EV volume, projecting EVs will account for 10% of total sales.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/42994308/rivian-joins-ford-tesla-in-supporting-relief-efforts-amid-california-wildfires", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T06:05:56", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-15", "summary": "Rivian deployed vehicles to support relief efforts for California wildfires, providing transport for supplies and offering free DC fast charging to owners within 150 miles of Los Angeles. Tesla and Ford also contributed; Tesla provided Cybertrucks for Starlink connectivity and Megapack chargers for power, while Ford issued grants to the Los Angeles Fire Department Foundation and the California Community Foundation.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/42993822/south-koreas-hyundai-kia-collectively-sold-more-evs-in-us-than-ford-in-2024", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T04:54:20", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-15", "summary": "In 2024, Hyundai and Kia collectively sold 117,826 EVs in the U.S., surpassing Ford's 97,865 units. Tesla remained the top-selling brand with approximately 634,000 units. GM's brands collectively sold 114,426 EVs. The Ioniq 5 was Hyundai's best-seller with over 44,000 units, ranking fourth overall, while the Tesla Cybertruck ranked fifth, ahead of the Ford F-150 Lightning.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/42993322/elon-musk-faces-sec-lawsuit-for-allegedly-hiding-twitter-stake-allowing-him-to-buy-shares-at-artificially-low-prices", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T02:10:29", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-15", "summary": "The SEC sued Elon Musk for failing to timely disclose his stake in Twitter (now X) in 2022. The lawsuit alleges that by March 2022, Musk had acquired over 5% of common stock without required disclosure, allowing him to purchase shares at artificially low prices and underpay investors by over $150 million. Musk eventually disclosed a 9% stake in April 2022, causing the stock price to rise by over 27%.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/42993086/microsoft-applied-digital-rigetti-computing-eli-lilly-tesla-why-these-5-stocks-are-on-investors-radars-today", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-15T01:41:39", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-15", "summary": "On Jan. 13, 2024, Tesla stock fell 1.72% to $396.36. While Cybertruck sales reached nearly 39,000 units in 2024, sales of the Model S and X declined. Other trending stocks included Microsoft (-0.36%), Applied Digital (+9.98% on $63.9 million revenue), Rigetti Computing (+47.93%), and Eli Lilly (-6.59% after reducing Q4 revenue guidance to $13.5 billion).", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/space/25/01/43046128/cathie-wood-adds-new-space-stock-to-2-etfs", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T23:33:28", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Ark Invest added Intuitive Machines (LUNR) to its ARKQ and ARKX ETFs, purchasing 267,642 and 160,178 shares respectively. To fund these, Ark sold shares of Rocket Lab and Kratos Defense. Tesla remains the largest holding in the ARKQ ETF at 15.44%. Intuitive Machines, which achieved the first private moon landing in February 2024, saw its stock rise over 600% in the past year and trades at $19.06.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/economics/macro-economic-events/25/01/43037588/stocks-pause-chipmakers-rise-gold-hits-2-month-highs-whats-driving-markets-thursday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T18:21:24", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Tesla shares fell 3.6% on Thursday following the announcement of price cuts for the Cybertruck to stimulate demand. Market activity was influenced by December retail sales rising 0.4% and jobless claims reaching 217,000. Gold reached a two-month high of $2,970 per ounce, while semiconductor stocks rose, with TSMC jumping over 5% following strong earnings.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 838, "out": 142}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/01/43036902/tesla-stock-valuation-analyst-flags-long-term-growth-opportunities-robotaxis-fsd", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T17:53:20", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Goldman Sachs analyst Mark Delaney maintained a Neutral rating on Tesla with a $345 price target. Delaney incorporated robotaxi revenue into his models, projecting operations to begin in the second half of 2026 and reach $115 million in 2027 based on a fleet of 1,500 vehicles. He noted improvements in FSD V13 but emphasized that Tesla needs significant progress to meet its goal of being safer than a human driver by 2Q25. The analyst remains cautious, citing full valuation and potential volatility in auto fundamentals and 2025 delivery volumes.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1007, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/options/25/01/43036504/9-consumer-discretionary-stocks-whale-activity-in-todays-session", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T17:35:30", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "On January 16, 2025, unusual options activity was recorded for Tesla (TSLA). A neutral call option sweep was observed with an expiration date of January 17, 2025, and a strike price of $420.00. A total of 125 contracts were traded across 7 separate trades, resulting in a total cost of $43.8K, with a price of $351.0 per contract. There were 16,813 open contracts at this strike prior to the activity, and 55,375 contracts were traded in total for the day.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1007, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43021809/trumps-nominee-for-dot-reportedly-wants-evs-to-pay-for-using-roads", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T09:04:39", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Sean Duffy, President-elect Donald Trump's nominee for Secretary of Transportation, stated during his confirmation hearing that electric vehicle owners should pay for road usage, though he acknowledged the implementation would be challenging. Duffy also pledged to continue safety investigations into Tesla if confirmed. The incoming administration has previously signaled intentions to end the $7,500 EV consumer tax credit.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1007, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43021419/palantirs-shyam-sankar-says-spacex-and-tesla-are-models-for-reviving-american-manufacturing-amid-rising-concerns-over-military-readiness", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T08:09:54", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Palantir CTO Shyam Sankar praised Tesla and SpaceX as models for revitalizing American manufacturing, highlighting Tesla's software-defined production line and SpaceX's vertical integration. Sankar contrasted these approaches with other companies that treat supply chains as a black box. He also expressed concerns regarding U.S. military readiness, noting production shortfalls in weapons systems.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1007, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43021093/tesla-offers-discounts-up-to-2000-on-new-inventory-cybertrucks", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T07:36:59", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Tesla is offering discounts of up to $2,000 on new non-foundation series Cybertrucks in its U.S. inventory, with demo vehicle discounts reaching up to $3,510. The base all-wheel drive variant starts at $78,390 for new inventory, while the premium Cyberbeast starts at $97,990. In 2024, Tesla sold 38,965 Cybertrucks, making it the company's third best-selling vehicle in the U.S.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1007, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43020202/trumps-dot-pick-assures-ongoing-tesla-fsd-investigation-and-rigorous-oversight-of-boeing", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T05:25:29", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Sean Duffy, Donald Trump's nominee for Secretary of Transportation, pledged during his Senate confirmation hearing to allow the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) to continue its investigation into Tesla's Full Self-Driving software. The probe, launched in October, covers approximately 2.4 million vehicles. Duffy also expressed support for reforming highway funding to capture revenue from EV users.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1007, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43019833/elon-musk-buying-tiktok-could-hurt-tesla-warns-gary-black-but-dan-ives-thinks-it-makes-sense", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T03:51:43", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Investor Gary Black warns that Elon Musk acquiring TikTok could negatively impact Tesla stock due to the potential need to sell billions in TSLA shares to fund the $40-$50 billion deal. Conversely, Wedbush analyst Dan Ives suggests the acquisition could align with Musk's relationships with the Trump administration and Beijing. TikTok has dismissed the acquisition reports as fiction. If no agreement is reached, TikTok faces a U.S. app store ban on January 19. Tesla stock closed at $428.22 on Wednesday, up 8.04%.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1110, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43019732/as-tesla-soars-8-gary-black-cites-trump-impact-elon-musk-pay-package-and-30k-car-as-key-catalysts-for-ev-maker-in-2025", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T03:15:30", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Tesla shares rose over 8% on Wednesday, closing at $428.22. Gary Black of The Future Fund identified key 2025 catalysts, including a new $30,000-$35,000 vehicle, potential regulatory support for autonomous driving under the Trump administration, and the Delaware Supreme Court's ruling on Musk's pay package. The Future Fund projects 2025 EPS of $3.70 and maintains a $380 price target. RBC raised its price target for Tesla to $440 from $313.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1110, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43019420/quantum-computing-taiwan-semiconductor-meta-intuitive-surgical-and-tesla-why-these-5-stocks-are-on-investors-radars-today", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-16T02:11:31", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-16", "summary": "Tesla stock rose 8.04% to close at $428.22, with a 52-week range of $138.80 to $488.54. The increase was supported by Kelley Blue Book data ranking the Model Y and Model 3 as top-selling EVs. Despite selling approximately 37,000 fewer cars in 2024 compared to 2023, Tesla maintained its EV market leadership amid rising competition.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1110, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/options/25/01/43063308/7-consumer-discretionary-stocks-with-whale-alerts-in-todays-session", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-17T17:35:22", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-18", "summary": "Unusual options activity for Tesla (TSLA) was recorded in the current session, featuring a bullish call option sweep expiring on January 17, 2025. Traders executed 46 contracts at a $430.00 strike price, split across 12 trades, with a total cost of $35.8K. The premium per contract was $780.0, with 21,469 open contracts prior to the activity.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1110, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/government/regulations/25/01/43056711/nvidia-unveils-ai-safety-tools-to-boost-enterprise-trust-ceo-jensen-to-miss-trump-inauguration", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-17T14:47:43", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk is among the Big Tech leaders expected to attend President-elect Donald Trump's inauguration on January 20. Meanwhile, Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang is expected to miss the event due to a routine East Asia tour. Nvidia recently launched NeMo Guardrails, a collection of software tools designed to help enterprises improve AI application safety and control.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1110, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43053982/taiwan-semiconductor-chief-calls-us-semiconductor-sanctions-manageable-to-skip-trump-inauguration", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-17T13:15:13", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk is scheduled to attend President-elect Donald Trump's inauguration on January 20. In contrast, Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (TSM) chief C.C. Wei will skip the event. TSM reported fourth-quarter revenue of $26.88 billion, up 38.8%, and projects 2025 capital expenditures between $38 billion and $42 billion.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1110, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43052360/sony-cancels-two-live-service-games-stays-committed-to-long-term-monetization", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-17T12:01:50", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Sony canceled unannounced live-service projects at Bend Studio and Bluepoint Games following a strategic review. Despite this, Sony remains committed to live-service games. In fiscal Q2 2024, Sony sold 3.8 million PS5 units, down from 4.9 million a year ago. Game & Network Services revenue rose 12% to 1.07 trillion yen, with operating income up 184% to 138.8 billion yen. Tesla CEO Elon Musk's xAI is developing an AI-driven game studio, positioning it against major studios he claims prioritize profit over creativity.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 854, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43050342/elon-musk-denies-teslas-involvement-in-fire-at-moss-landing-power-plant-in-monterey-county", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-17T09:52:49", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk denied that Tesla's Megapack energy storage products were involved in a fire at a 3000 MWh battery storage facility in Moss Landing, Monterey County, on January 16, 2025. The facility is operated by Vistra Energy. While a separate Pacific Gas & Electric Megapack system at Moss Landing caught fire in late 2022, Musk stated the current incident is unrelated to Tesla.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 854, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43049428/tesla-says-it-is-working-on-a-more-comprehensive-cleaning-solution-for-cybertruck-rear-view-camera", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-17T08:08:34", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Tesla is developing a more comprehensive cleaning solution for the Cybertruck's rear-view camera after drivers requested an automated option. Currently, only the front-facing camera has a sprayer nozzle, while the rear camera requires manual cleaning. This comes as Tesla works toward autonomous driving via its Full Self-Driving (FSD) technology. The NHTSA is currently investigating 2.4 million Tesla vehicles regarding FSD performance in low-visibility conditions.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 854, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43048579/tesla-extends-free-lifetime-supercharging-offer-on-foundation-series-cybertruck-till-jan-end", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-17T06:22:58", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-17", "summary": "Tesla extended its free lifetime supercharging offer for Foundation Series Cybertrucks in its inventory to January 31. The offer applies to orders placed on or after December 27. The Foundation Series, which features premium accessories and laser-etched badges, starts at $99,990. In 2024, the Cybertruck was Tesla's third best-selling vehicle in the U.S., with 38,965 units sold.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 854, "out": 126}}
