{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43078297/teslas-vietnamese-rival-vinfast-enters-indias-ev-market-amid-global-expansion-push-plans-500-million-investment", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-20T03:30:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-20", "summary": "Vietnamese EV maker VinFast is expanding into India, its 'next growth frontier,' with plans to invest $500 million over five years to build a factory with an initial capacity of 50,000 units annually. The company unveiled its VF6 and VF7 models at the India Auto Show. VinFast reported 21,912 vehicle deliveries in Q3 2024, a 115% year-over-year increase, and secured $3.5 billion in potential funding through 2026, including $2.1 billion from CEO Pham Nhat Vuong.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 121}}
