{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/social-media/25/01/43088960/trump-suspends-us-tiktok-ban-for-75-days-with-executive-order-but-legal-and-market-uncertainty-looms-over-platforms-future", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-21T05:35:17", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-21", "summary": "President Trump issued an executive order suspending the TikTok ban for 75 days. Potential acquirers include Perplexity and Elon Musk's X platform, though investor Gary Black warned a TikTok acquisition could negatively impact Tesla's stock. TikTok generated $12.34 billion in U.S. ad revenue in 2024.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 801, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/global/25/01/43088582/gary-black-questions-elon-musks-take-on-ev-credit-removal-after-tesla-sales-drop-in-europe-not-sure-how-the-math-works", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-21T03:32:06", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-21", "summary": "Gary Black of The Future Fund LLC questioned the bullish outlook regarding the potential removal of the $7,500 U.S. EV tax credit, citing Tesla's 2024 year-over-year sales declines of 34% in France and 41% in Germany following similar subsidy eliminations. Tesla researcher Troy Teslike noted that without the credit, Tesla vehicles would effectively cost $7,500 more than luxury gas-powered competitors. Tesla reported 1.79 million global deliveries in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023. While Elon Musk has previously stated that ending subsidies would have a 'slight' impact on Tesla, Teslike suggests a six-month phase-out would be optimal for sales performance.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1439, "out": 158}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/analyst-ratings/25/01/43146836/tesla-stock-a-deep-dive-into-analyst-perspectives-32-ratings", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-22T22:01:59", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-23", "summary": "In the past three months, 32 analysts provided ratings for Tesla, with 20 bullish or somewhat bullish, 9 indifferent, and 3 bearish. The average 12-month price target is $358.81, a 27% increase from the previous $282.53. Recent actions include upgrades from firms like Wedbush (target $550), Piper Sandler (target $500), and Morgan Stanley (target $430), while GLJ Research maintains a $24.86 target. Tesla reported 2024 global deliveries slightly below 1.8 million, with a 7.85% revenue growth rate as of September 30, 2024, an 8.61% net margin, and a 0.18 debt-to-equity ratio.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1439, "out": 158}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43138517/chipmakers-rally-on-ai-stargate-bet-netflix-soar-bitcoin-falters-amid-trumps-crypto-silence-whats-driving-markets-wednesday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-22T18:11:39", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-23", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk questioned the financial viability of the $500 billion 'Stargate Project' announced by OpenAI, Oracle, and SoftBank, stating the founders 'don't actually have the money.' The project aims to develop AI infrastructure in the U.S. over four years. Meanwhile, tech stocks rallied on Wednesday, with the iShares Semiconductor ETF rising 2.3%. Other market movements included Netflix shares climbing 12% following strong earnings, while Bitcoin fell nearly 2% to $104,000 amid a lack of crypto-related commentary from the new administration.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1439, "out": 158}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43134430/jamie-dimon-plans-to-help-elon-musk-as-much-as-he-can", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-22T16:17:40", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-23", "summary": "JPMorgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon stated he has 'hugged it out' with Tesla CEO Elon Musk, resolving past differences including a lawsuit over stock warrants that JPMorgan dropped last year. Dimon praised Musk's success at Tesla, SpaceX, and Neuralink, calling him 'our Einstein,' and expressed a desire to assist Musk's companies and his role in the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE).", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1439, "out": 158}}
