{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43214246/researcher-expects-teslas-vehicle-deliveries-to-remain-flat-in-2025-contrary-to-musks-20-30-growth-prediction", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-25T01:46:58", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-25", "summary": "Researcher Troy Teslike predicts Tesla will deliver 1.8 million vehicles in 2025, matching 2024 levels, contradicting CEO Elon Musk's 20-30% growth forecast. Teslike expects a new, affordable model priced under $30,000 (after a $7,500 federal tax credit) in the second half of 2025. Tesla delivered 1.79 million vehicles in 2024. Recent price adjustments include a 25% increase for the refreshed Model Y in the U.S. and price hikes in China and Canada.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 751, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/legal/25/01/43219350/elizabeth-warren-to-elon-musk-cut-unnecessary-federal-cannabis-enforcement-and-save-billions", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-26T20:40:25", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-27", "summary": "Senator Elizabeth Warren sent a letter to Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) chair Elon Musk proposing federal spending cuts of over $2 trillion. Her recommendations include reducing federal enforcement against marijuana users and businesses, which she labels wasteful. Warren cited FBI data showing marijuana possession arrests account for roughly 25% of all drug possession arrests and noted the DEA eradicated over 5.7 million plants in 2022.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 751, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43219136/cuban-on-musk-i-have-no-problem-throwing-elon-under-the-bus-but-ill-save-it-for-when-its-truly-deserved", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-26T19:00:33", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-27", "summary": "Entrepreneur Mark Cuban defended Tesla CEO Elon Musk's online behavior, describing it as \"kind of insane\" but consistent with his personality. Cuban noted that while he is willing to criticize Musk when deserved, he views Musk's controversial social media posts as typical banter. Musk has previously faced a $40 million SEC settlement over a tweet and a Secret Service investigation regarding remarks about Donald Trump.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 751, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/social-media/25/01/43219015/elon-musk-faces-criticism-from-biographer-over-auschwitz-visit-he-truly-is-a-sociopath", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-26T17:45:43", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-27", "summary": "Biographer Seth Abramson labeled Elon Musk a \"sociopath\" following the re-emergence of images from Musk's January 2024 visit to Auschwitz. The criticism follows recent scrutiny regarding a gesture Musk made after Donald Trump's inauguration, which some observers compared to a Nazi salute, a claim Musk dismissed as propaganda.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 751, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43218782/bill-gates-i-would-probably-be-diagnosed-on-the-autism-spectrum-if-growing-up-today", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-26T16:00:43", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-27", "summary": "In his upcoming memoir, Bill Gates suggests he would likely be diagnosed on the autism spectrum if he were a child today. Gates reflects on his childhood challenges, including missing social cues and obsessive focus on projects. He joins other business leaders like Elon Musk and Richard Branson in discussing neurodivergence.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 751, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43218654/trumps-ev-policy-shakes-market-teslas-upcoming-fsd-upgrade-and-inside-trumps-1-5m-beast-this-week-in-mobility", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-26T15:00:40", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-26", "summary": "The EV market faces uncertainty following President Trump's inauguration and potential changes to the $7,500 federal tax credit. Researcher Troy Teslike outlined scenarios ranging from restricted eligibility to total cancellation within six months. Gary Black of The Future Fund expressed concern over the impact of removing incentives on Tesla's sales. Additionally, Elon Musk hinted that FSD-equipped vehicles will soon gain the ability to reverse automatically.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 751, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/01/43218481/elon-musks-shocking-remarks-to-far-right-german-party-too-much-focus-on-past-guilt", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-26T14:15:17", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-26", "summary": "Elon Musk appeared via video at a rally for Germany's far-right AfD party, urging voters to prioritize national self-determination over European Union influence and to move beyond guilt regarding Germany's fascist past. Musk's endorsement of the nationalist, anti-immigration party comes four weeks before German elections and follows recent controversies regarding his public conduct.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 751, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/global/25/01/43251316/tesla-faces-boycott-call-in-poland-over-musks-wwii-comments", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-27T21:09:55", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Tesla faces a potential boycott in Poland after CEO Elon Musk made comments downplaying Germany's past at a rally for the Alternative for Germany party. Polish Sports and Tourism Minister Slawomir Nitras urged citizens to stop buying Teslas, citing the 80th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz. Tesla is currently the bestselling EV brand in Poland, with 4,460 units sold in 2024. Additionally, Tesla's global brand value fell 26% to $43 billion in 2025, and surveys in the Netherlands indicate that Musk's persona is negatively impacting brand loyalty and consideration.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1286, "out": 153}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/01/43246903/tesla-analysts-top-5-items-to-watch-in-q4-earnings-will-refreshed-model-y-new-evs-help-growth", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-27T19:17:36", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Goldman Sachs analyst Mark Delaney maintains a Neutral rating on Tesla with a $345 price target ahead of Q4 earnings on January 29. Key items to watch include automotive non-GAAP gross margins, 2025 delivery outlook, FSD progress, and the refreshed Model Y. Tesla is targeting 20% to 30% year-over-year delivery growth for 2025. Delaney noted that Tesla's U.S. market share dropped to the mid-40% range in Q4, while European market share fell to 13%. The analyst also highlighted concerns regarding the potential end of the $7,500 federal tax credit and the timeline for the Cybercab robotaxi.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1286, "out": 153}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/etfs/sector-etfs/25/01/43244039/ironhold-capital-cio-reveals-trends-hedge-funds-track-4-etfs-to-watch", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-27T17:59:27", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Siddharth Singhai, CIO of IronHold Capital, identified the U.S. auto industry as a sector to watch, noting that protectionist policies under the Trump administration could benefit General Motors, Ford, and Stellantis by mitigating cost disadvantages against Chinese EVs. Singhai suggested investors be cautious of auto companies vulnerable to the EV transition. The First Trust S-Network Future Vehicles & Tech ETF (CARZ), which includes Tesla, Ford, GM, and Stellantis, is highlighted as a tool for exposure to domestic automotive manufacturing growth.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1286, "out": 153}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/01/43239042/magnificent-seven-broadcom-lose-nearly-900-billion-in-value-as-deepseek-sparks-ai-carnage-why-this-expert-is-still-bullish-on-us-tech", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-27T16:07:49", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "The emergence of China's DeepSeek R1 AI model triggered a market selloff, erasing nearly $900 billion in value from major tech stocks in 30 minutes. Tesla's market cap declined by $30.92 billion, or 0.98%. Despite the volatility, some analysts remain bullish, arguing that the development of competitive AI models accelerates the path to AGI and will not reduce capital expenditures by major tech firms. Tesla is scheduled to report its Q4 earnings on January 29 after the market close, with an EPS estimate of $0.74 and a revenue estimate of $27.13 billion.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1286, "out": 153}}
