{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/media/25/01/43220499/despite-peter-thiel-ties-jd-vance-warns-of-big-tech-billionaires-excessive-clout-theyve-got-too-much-power", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-27T05:45:42", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-27", "summary": "Vice President JD Vance, supported by Peter Thiel, criticized big tech companies for having 'too much power' during an appearance on 'Face the Nation.' Despite tech CEOs like Elon Musk (Tesla), Mark Zuckerberg (Meta), Jeff Bezos (Amazon), Tim Cook (Apple), and Sundar Pichai (Alphabet) attending Donald Trump's inauguration, Vance stated they did not receive preferential treatment. Vance emphasized that the administration expects tech companies to respect constitutional rights and halt censorship, noting his desire to break up large tech firms like Alphabet.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1029, "out": 133}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43219987/tesla-could-drop-over-13-due-to-trumps-potential-ev-tax-credit-cuts-fsd-and-delivery-concerns-says-gary-black", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-27T02:18:31", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-27", "summary": "Tesla faces conflicting 2025 delivery forecasts, with Wall Street projecting 2.07 million units (16% growth) while forecaster Troy Teslike predicts a 1% decline. CEO Elon Musk previously guided for 20-30% growth. Gary Black warns that potential elimination of the $7,500 federal EV tax credit could disproportionately impact Tesla, potentially pushing the stock down 13% to the $350-$375 range. Wedbush analyst Dan Ives maintains a $550 price target, citing autonomous driving potential. Tesla stock closed at $406.58 on Friday.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1029, "out": 133}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43219913/jeff-bezos-backed-perplexity-ai-proposes-deal-to-merge-with-tiktok-giving-us-government-50-stake-report", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-27T01:45:20", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-27", "summary": "Perplexity AI, backed by Jeff Bezos, has proposed a revised merger with TikTok's U.S. operations, offering the U.S. government a 50% stake via a $300 billion IPO. The proposal would allow ByteDance to retain ties to the app without the proprietary recommendation algorithm. President Donald Trump previously suggested Elon Musk or Larry Ellison could take ownership of TikTok. Reports indicate increased censorship on the platform following a Trump executive order.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1029, "out": 133}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/etfs/sector-etfs/25/01/43291535/magnificent-7-earnings-ahead-3-etfs-to-ride-the-wave", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T23:30:08", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-29", "summary": "The 'Magnificent 7' stocks (Apple, Microsoft, Alphabet, Amazon, NVIDIA, Tesla, Meta) are the focus of the current earnings season, with expected 18% earnings growth in 2025. Tesla, Microsoft, and Meta report earnings Wednesday, followed by Apple (Feb 4), Alphabet and Amazon (Feb 6), and Nvidia (later in February). ETFs like MAGS, FNGS, and MGK offer exposure to these companies. Tesla recently missed Q4 delivery estimates and reported its first-ever year-over-year decline in annual vehicle deliveries.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1029, "out": 133}}
