{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/government/25/01/43271607/recent-filing-shows-that-rep-marjorie-taylor-greene-bought-over-4k-worth-of-tesla-stock", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T15:02:32", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Representative Marjorie Taylor Greene filed a purchase of Tesla (TSLA) stock on January 27, 2025, valued between $4,004 and $60,000. This follows a series of other recent stock trades by the Representative, including purchases of Adobe, Amazon, and Applied Materials in late 2024. The article notes that congressional transactions are disclosed per the STOCK Act, which prohibits the use of private information for personal gain.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43260646/microsoft-eyes-tiktok-us-deal-as-trump-confirms-acquisition-talks-are-underway", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T11:16:49", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "President Donald Trump stated that Microsoft is in talks to acquire the U.S. arm of TikTok. Other potential bidders include Perplexity and Frank McCourt. The report notes that in 2020, Microsoft and Oracle were contenders for a TikTok acquisition, and mentions that Oracle co-founder Larry Ellison and Tesla CEO Elon Musk have emerged as potential contenders for a deal that could value TikTok at $1 trillion.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/01/43259982/tesla-earnings-delivery-outlook-model-y-ramp-up-optimus-bot-in-focus-say-analysts", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T10:58:22", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Morgan Stanley analysts expect Tesla's upcoming earnings call to focus on the 20-30% delivery growth target, Model Y production ramp-up, Full Self-Driving (FSD) improvements, and Optimus robot milestones. Analysts project 2025 volume growth closer to 10% rather than 30% due to EV market pressures and competition. Morgan Stanley maintains an 'overweight' rating with a $430 price target. Tesla reports Q4 and full-year 2024 results on Wednesday at 5:30 p.m. ET.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43259304/trumps-proposed-corporate-tax-cuts-could-boost-teslas-fy25-eps-by-4-says-analyst", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T09:49:58", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Gary Black, Managing Partner at The Future Fund, estimates that a reduction in the U.S. corporate tax rate from 21% to 15% could boost Tesla's FY25 EPS by $0.12, a 4% increase. Tesla reported 1.79 million vehicle deliveries in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023. The company is scheduled to report 2024 financial results on Wednesday.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43258774/unsupervised-fsd-to-optimus-robot-top-questions-investors-want-answers-to-from-elon-musk-led-tesla-ahead-of-q4-earnings", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T08:36:36", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Ahead of Tesla's Q4 and full-year 2024 earnings report on Wednesday, shareholders have submitted questions regarding the timeline for unsupervised FSD in Texas and California, potential FSD licensing to other automakers, and the production and pricing of the Optimus robot. Elon Musk has previously targeted 2025 for low-volume production of Optimus for internal use, with potential sales prices between $10,000 and $20,000.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 121}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/government/regulations/25/01/43258090/gamestop-short-seller-wants-freedom-of-speech-for-millions-having-stock-market-conversations-questioning-sec-on-what-protects-honest-opinions", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T07:28:54", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Citron Research founder Andrew Left filed a petition with the SEC seeking protection for free speech in online stock market discussions. The petition, filed by Dynamis LLP, argues that current regulatory actions create a chilling effect on market participation. Left, who faced SEC fraud charges in July 2024 regarding his commentary on stocks including Tesla, Nvidia, and Meta, is requesting clear guidelines on trading windows, disclaimer safe harbors, and the scope of trading restrictions. The petition notes that Citron suffered significant losses during the 2021 GameStop short squeeze.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 939, "out": 145}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43257819/tesla-got-over-70000-orders-for-new-model-y-in-china-in-five-days-report", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T06:42:41", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Tesla received over 70,000 orders for its refreshed Model Y in China within five days of its launch. The new model is priced at 263,500 yuan ($36,340), approximately 5.4% higher than the previous version. Deliveries are expected to begin in March, pending regulatory approval. Tesla plans to suspend parts of its Model Y production lines from Jan. 22 to Feb. 14 to prepare for increased output. This follows Tesla's 2024 global delivery report of 1.79 million vehicles, a decline from 1.81 million in 2023.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 939, "out": 145}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43256925/chamath-palihapitiya-warns-of-ai-shift-the-battle-is-now-more-about-ai-inference-vs-training-as-deepseek-sparks-nvidia-selloff", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T03:33:56", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Billionaire investor Chamath Palihapitiya warned that the AI industry is shifting focus from training to inference capabilities following Chinese startup DeepSeek's release of a cost-efficient LLM. Palihapitiya, who holds a stake in Groq, argued that the U.S. should prioritize global inference infrastructure. He noted that while Nvidia faces high risk from this shift, Tesla remains the least exposed among major tech stocks. DeepSeek-V3 reportedly cost $5.57 million to train, significantly less than traditional industry costs.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 939, "out": 145}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43256648/cathie-wood-swoops-in-to-buy-amd-shares-amid-deepseek-tech-upheaval-dumps-tesla-stock-worth-8-1-million", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T02:40:24", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "On Jan. 27, 2025, Cathie Wood's Ark Invest sold 20,392 shares of Tesla through the ARKW ETF, valued at approximately $8.1 million. The sale occurred as Tesla's stock fell 2.32% to $397.15 amid concerns over potential electric vehicle tax credit cuts under the Trump administration and diverging 2025 delivery growth forecasts. Additionally, Ark Invest purchased $4.89 million in AMD shares and $1.76 million in Amazon shares, while selling $4.55 million in Palantir shares.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 939, "out": 145}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43256560/nvidia-faces-investor-panic-as-chinas-deepseek-emerges-but-top-analyst-predicts-higher-ai-infrastructure-demand-despite-market-jitters-the-market-is-overreacting-to-deepseeks-success", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T02:17:01", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "Deepwater Asset Management's Gene Munster stated that the market is overreacting to the success of Chinese AI startup DeepSeek, which trained its V3 model for under $6 million using Nvidia H800 chips. Munster argued that efficient training methods could actually increase AI infrastructure investment. He noted that market volatility will likely persist until earnings reports from Microsoft, Meta, and Tesla are released. Nvidia's stock dropped 17% on Monday, falling below its 200-day moving average for the first time in two years.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 939, "out": 145}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43256325/nvidia-broadcom-nebius-group-taiwan-semiconductor-and-tesla-why-these-5-stocks-are-on-investors-radars-today", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-28T01:42:05", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-28", "summary": "On Monday, Tesla shares fell 2.32% to close at $397.15, with an intraday range between $389 and $406.69. The stock's 52-week high is $488.54 and its low is $138.80. The decline was attributed to diverging forecasts for the company's 2025 delivery growth, influenced by uncertainty regarding new vehicle launches and potential policy changes. Other tech stocks, including Nvidia, Broadcom, and Nebius Group, also saw significant declines following the emergence of DeepSeek's cost-efficient AI model.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 939, "out": 145}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/earnings/25/01/43321103/tesla-q4-earnings-highlights-revenue-miss-eps-miss-ev-updates-automaker-says-2025-will-be-a-seminal-year", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-29T21:41:59", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Tesla reported Q4 revenue of $25.71 billion (up 2% YoY) and EPS of 73 cents, both missing Street estimates. Automotive revenue fell 8% YoY to $19.8 billion. While 2024 deliveries reached 1.79 million, this marked the first annual decline in company history. Tesla deployed 11.0 GWh of energy storage in Q4. The company expects 2025 to be a 'seminal year' with a return to vehicle growth, FSD launches in the U.S., and new affordable models starting production in the first half of 2025. Cybercab volume production is targeted for 2026. Tesla ended the quarter with $1.07 billion in digital assets.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1150, "out": 128}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/economics/macro-economic-events/25/01/43318325/a-different-powell-emerges-fed-chair-softens-hawkish-tone-on-interest-rates-bitcoin", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-29T20:56:56", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Fed Chair Jerome Powell maintained interest rates at 4.25%-4.50% and adopted a more measured, cautious tone compared to December. Powell sidestepped political pressure regarding rate cuts from President Trump and criticism from Elon Musk. Regarding Bitcoin, Powell signaled a shift in stance, stating banks are able to serve crypto customers if they manage risks, and expressed support for greater regulatory clarity.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1150, "out": 128}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/global/25/01/43315374/ai-etfs-in-focus-as-alibaba-challenges-deepseek-with-new-model", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-29T18:50:50", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Alibaba launched its Qwen 2.5-Max AI model on Jan. 29, claiming it outperforms DeepSeek-V3, GPT-4.0, and Llama-3.1-405B. This intensifies the AI competition, impacting investor focus on AI-exposed ETFs. The ARK Autonomous Technology & Robotics ETF (ARKQ) includes Tesla, Nvidia, and other AI-centric firms with a 0.75% expense ratio. Other ETFs mentioned include AIQ (0.68% expense ratio) and Invesco QQQ.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1150, "out": 128}}
