{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43295163/elon-musk-says-unsupervised-full-self-driving-begins-as-tesla-can-now-drive-itself-from-factory-to-loading-docks", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-29T07:18:42", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-29", "summary": "Tesla announced that its vehicles can now autonomously navigate from the factory to loading dock lanes without human involvement, a development Elon Musk described as the beginning of 'unsupervised full self-driving.' This follows a January 2025 NHTSA probe into 2.6 million Tesla vehicles regarding FSD and the 'Actually Smart Summon' feature. Musk previously predicted FSD would surpass human driving safety by Q2 2025.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1109, "out": 114}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43293715/cathie-wood-dumps-tesla-stock-ahead-of-q4-earnings-ark-invest-loads-up-on-amazon", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-29T02:33:33", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-29", "summary": "On January 28, 2025, Cathie Wood's Ark Invest sold 2,772 shares of Tesla (valued at approximately $1.1 million) through the ARK Next Generation Internet ETF (ARKW) ahead of the company's Q4 earnings report. Simultaneously, Ark Invest purchased 41,338 shares of Amazon for approximately $9.8 million.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1109, "out": 114}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43293219/teslas-30k-ev-risks-being-a-nothing-burger-says-gary-black-warns-of-cannibalization-without-a-new-compact-design", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-29T01:40:28", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-29", "summary": "Gary Black of The Future Fund warned that Tesla's planned $30,000-$35,000 EV could cause significant cannibalization if it lacks a new compact form factor. Tesla delivered 1.79 million vehicles in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023. Morgan Stanley projects 2025 delivery growth of 10-20%, below Musk's 20-30% guidance. Goldman Sachs maintains a $345 price target, while Bank of America downgraded Tesla to Neutral with a $490 price target.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1109, "out": 114}}
