{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/01/43347509/tesla-stock-analysts-highlight-fsd-robotaxis-new-vehicles-for-growth-elon-has-never-sounded-so-bullish", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T17:49:02", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-31", "summary": "Following Q4 results, analysts provided varied outlooks: Bank of America (Neutral, $490 PT), Goldman Sachs (Neutral, $345 PT), Needham (Hold), RBC Capital (Outperform, $440 PT), Cantor Fitzgerald (Neutral, raised PT to $425), Piper Sandler (Overweight, $500 PT), Stifel (Buy, $492 PT), and Morgan Stanley (Overweight, $430 PT). Key takeaways included confirmation of a low-cost vehicle for 2025, progress on unsupervised FSD, and Optimus Bot updates. While some analysts noted weak gross margins and production downtime for the Model Y transition, others highlighted Musk's bullish tone regarding AI and robotics.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1418, "out": 113}}
