{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43330939/elon-musks-ev-giant-rises-in-thursday-premarket-despite-tesla-bear-saying-80-of-its-cars-cannot-operate-using-fsd", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T11:28:26", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "TSLA stock rose over 3% in pre-market trading despite missing fourth-quarter revenue estimates. CEO Elon Musk admitted that existing HW3 computers in 80% of Tesla vehicles must be replaced to support full self-driving (FSD) capabilities. GLJ Research's Gordon L. Johnson questioned the future compatibility of FSD with HW4 and HW5 hardware. Tesla shares have risen 103% over the past year.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1502, "out": 102}}
