{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43329365/a-day-after-elon-musk-hailed-teslas-unsupervised-fsd-ross-gerber-criticizes-ev-makers-autonomous-driving-system-doesnt-work-when-dust-or-ash-get-in-the-cameras", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T09:51:00", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Investor Ross Gerber criticized Tesla's vision-only Full Self-Driving (FSD) system on January 29, 2025, citing failures due to dust, ash, and sun glare. Despite Tesla's recent announcement that vehicles can navigate from factory to loading docks autonomously, the company faces a National Highway Traffic Safety Administration probe into 2.6 million vehicles. CEO Elon Musk maintains that FSD will surpass human safety by Q2 2025, while Tesla reported Q4 revenue of $25.71 billion, missing analyst estimates.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43328898/elon-musk-warns-teslas-new-model-y-will-result-in-several-weeks-of-lost-production-for-ev-giant-in-q1", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T08:46:30", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "CEO Elon Musk announced that all Tesla factories will begin producing the new Model Y in February, resulting in several weeks of lost production in Q1 due to retooling. Deliveries are scheduled for March. Tesla reported 1.79 million global vehicle deliveries in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023. The company also warned that operating expenses, which totaled $10.37 billion in 2024, are expected to increase in 2025 to support growth initiatives.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43328477/tesla-apple-and-3-stocks-to-watch-heading-into-thursday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T08:05:39", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Tesla shares rose 4.1% to $405.23 in after-hours trading following its Q4 earnings report. While the company missed earnings and sales expectations, it committed to returning to vehicle growth in 2025, launching new 'more affordable' models in the first half of 2025, and licensing its FSD software to rivals.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43327837/tesla-ceo-elon-musk-dismises-lidar-again-says-if-humans-drive-without-shooting-lasers-from-their-eyes-so-can-autonomous-cars", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T07:00:45", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "During the Q4 earnings call, CEO Elon Musk reiterated his stance that LiDAR is the 'wrong solution' for autonomous driving, comparing human vision to cameras and neural nets. While Tesla removed ultrasonic sensors in 2022 and relies solely on cameras, critics like Zoox co-founder Jesse Levinson argue that additional hardware is necessary for safety. Waymo continues to utilize LiDAR in its robotaxis.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43327268/tesla-expects-50-surge-in-energy-storage-deployments-for-2025-after-segment-revenue-doubles-in-q4", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T05:51:35", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Tesla's energy generation and storage segment revenue rose 113% to over $3 billion in Q4, with a record 11.0 GWh deployed. The company expects energy storage deployment to grow at least 50% year-over-year in 2025. Conversely, automotive revenue dipped 8% to $19.8 billion. Tesla operates a Megafactory in Lathrop, California, and is building another in Shanghai, expected to ship Megapacks in Q1 2025.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43326943/elon-musk-is-kind-of-glad-many-didnt-pick-up-a-tesla-fsd-subscription-heres-why", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T04:42:35", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "CEO Elon Musk stated that Tesla will likely need to upgrade the Hardware 3 computers of customers who purchased FSD to achieve fully unsupervised autonomous driving. The company reported Q4 operating expenses of $2.60 billion, a 9% year-on-year increase, and 2024 capital expenditure of $11.34 billion. Despite missing Q4 revenue and earnings estimates, the stock rose up to 5% after-hours on promises of new models and autonomous vehicle deployment.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/01/43326143/tesla-stock-rises-5-after-hours-on-fsd-and-new-vehicle-promises-despite-q4-revenue-miss", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T02:51:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Tesla stock rose 5% after-hours following promises to launch 'more affordable' models in the first half of 2025 and plans to license FSD software to other automakers. The company plans to start testing autonomous ride-hailing in Texas in June and aims to launch unsupervised FSD in California by the end of 2025. Tesla reported Q4 revenue, EPS, and gross margins below expectations.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43326118/tesla-meta-microsoft-ibm-nvidia-why-these-5-stocks-are-on-investors-radars-today", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T02:47:24", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "On January 29, 2025, Tesla stock fell 2.26% to close at $389.10 but rose over 4% in after-hours trading. The company reported Q4 revenue of $25.71 billion, missing the $27.26 billion consensus estimate. The stock's 52-week range is $138.80 to $488.54. The broader market declined as the Federal Reserve kept interest rates unchanged in the 4.25% to 4.5% range.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 747, "out": 123}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/01/43326062/gary-black-calls-teslas-austin-robotaxi-launch-by-june-most-bullish-takeaway-but-wants-answers-on-auto-margins-and-next-gen-ev", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T02:38:27", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Tesla bull Gary Black praised the planned June launch of paid autonomous ride-hailing in Austin as the most bullish takeaway from the Q4 earnings call. However, he expressed concerns regarding low automotive gross margins of 13.6% (excluding regulatory credits) and the form factor of the upcoming $30,000-$35,000 vehicle, warning that it must not cannibalize existing sales. Tesla reported Q4 revenue of $25.71 billion, missing the $27.26 billion estimate, and a 2024 delivery decline to 1.79 million vehicles. The company plans new vehicle production in the first half of 2025 and Cybercab volume production in 2026.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 923, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43325891/backed-by-youtube-king-mrbeast-group-of-american-investors-including-roblox-ceo-lock-in-over-20-billion-for-tiktok-takeover-but-they-have-not-heard-back-directly-from-bytedance", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T02:23:44", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "A group of U.S. investors, including MrBeast and Roblox CEO David Baszucki, has secured over $20 billion for a potential TikTok takeover. While ByteDance has stated TikTok's U.S. business is not for sale, other potential contenders mentioned include Microsoft, Oracle co-founder Larry Ellison, and Tesla CEO Elon Musk. Analyst Dan Ives estimates a potential sale value between $40 billion and $50 billion.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 923, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43325888/tesla-likely-to-sell-optimus-to-rival-companies-in-2026-price-point-of-humanoid-robot-to-be-detemined-by-demand-says-ceo-elon-musk", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T02:23:13", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk announced plans to produce several thousand Optimus humanoid robots this year for internal factory use, with a next-generation version slated for launch mid-next year for sale to rival companies. Musk projected long-term revenue potential for Optimus to exceed $10 trillion. While production costs are expected to drop below $20,000 at scale, pricing will be market-driven. Tesla also confirmed the start of production for new, more affordable vehicle models in the first half of 2025.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 923, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/01/43325381/elon-musks-tesla-racks-up-600-million-paper-gains-on-bitcoin-in-q4", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-30T01:33:26", "effective_trading_date": "2025-01-30", "summary": "Tesla reported an unrealized gain of $600 million on its cryptocurrency holdings in Q4, following a new accounting standard that allows firms to report holdings at market value. Tesla's digital assets on its balance sheet rose to $1.07 billion, with holdings of 11,509 BTC. This gain accounted for 26% of the company's total income for the quarter. Tesla reported Q4 revenue of $25.71 billion, up 2% year-over-year.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 923, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/trading-ideas/25/01/43403758/exclusive-this-magnificent-7-stock-will-feel-the-pinch-of-feds-rate-decision-poll-shows", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-31T20:54:46", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-01", "summary": "In a Benzinga reader poll, 39% of respondents identified Tesla as the Magnificent 7 stock most negatively impacted by the Federal Reserve's decision to keep interest rates steady at 4.25% to 4.5% in January. The poll suggests this is due to Tesla's higher-priced products and sensitivity to borrowing rates. Economists currently predict the first rate cut may not occur until June or later.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 923, "out": 126}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/economics/macro-economic-events/25/01/43400100/tech-stocks-rally-sp-500-flirts-with-records-gold-extends-all-time-highs-whats-driving-markets-friday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-01-31T17:57:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-01", "summary": "Major U.S. stock indices recovered from Monday's losses, with tech stocks leading the rally on Friday. Tesla and Amazon were primary drivers of the Magnificent Seven's 1.6% gain. The S&P 500 reached 6,118 points, nearing its all-time high. Meanwhile, gold prices exceeded $2,800 per ounce, and Bitcoin held steady at $104,800.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 923, "out": 126}}
