{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43419132/tesla-begins-global-production-of-refreshed-model-y-deliveries-start-in-march", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-01T09:47:02", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-01", "summary": "Tesla has begun global production of the refreshed Model Y across its four factories in Berlin, Shanghai, Texas, and Fremont. Deliveries are scheduled to start in March in both China and the U.S. CEO Elon Musk noted that retooling for this simultaneous global update will cause several weeks of lost production in Q1 and impact margins. Tesla reported 1.79 million global deliveries in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 891, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43423390/trumps-tax-cuts-could-boost-teslas-earnings-rivian-ceo-unfazed-by-ev-tax-credit-concerns-and-more-this-week-in-mobility", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-02T15:30:17", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-02", "summary": "Gary Black suggests a corporate tax rate reduction from 21% to 15% could increase Tesla's FY25 EPS by $0.12, or 4%. Ross Gerber criticized Tesla's Full Self-Driving, favoring Waymo's robotaxi technology. Rivian CEO RJ Scaringe stated that eliminating the $7,500 EV tax credit would be a minor speed bump for the sector. A Polish official called for a Tesla boycott due to Elon Musk's comments at a German political rally. Musk announced plans to produce several thousand Optimus humanoid robots this year for internal factory use, with long-term revenue potential estimated at over $10 trillion.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 973, "out": 152}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43449494/tesla-vs-jpmorgan-battle-of-growth-vs-value-would-see-tsla-at-3284-and-jpm-at-313966-if-pes-reversed", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T21:34:48", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-04", "summary": "Tesla, valued at $1.24 trillion, reported FY2024 net income of $8.4 billion and EPS of $2.42, resulting in a P/E ratio of 159.0. In contrast, JPMorgan Chase, with a $749.15 billion market cap, reported $58.5 billion in net income and $19.75 EPS, yielding a P/E of 13.6. Analysts and investors like Cathie Wood argue Tesla should be valued as a high-growth tech and autonomous taxi platform company rather than a traditional automaker, citing potential in AI, robotics, and FSD.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 973, "out": 152}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/trading-ideas/25/02/43447273/tesla-sales-drop-12-in-california-is-elon-musks-support-for-donald-trump-hurting-ev-sales", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T20:12:00", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-04", "summary": "Tesla's 2024 sales in California dropped 12% overall and 8% in Q4, with Model 3 registrations falling 36% year-over-year. Tesla's U.S. market share declined from 55% in 2023 to 48.7% in 2024, with 633,762 total vehicles sold, a 5.6% decrease. Brand Finance reported Tesla's brand value fell $15 billion in 2024, dropping from 18th to 36th place in 2025. Reports suggest consumer sentiment may be impacted by Elon Musk's political support for Donald Trump.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 973, "out": 152}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43444972/whats-going-on-with-tesla-stock-monday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T18:40:36", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-04", "summary": "Tesla shares fell 6% to $380.19 on Monday following President Trump's announcement of 25% tariffs on Canadian and Mexican imports and 10% on Chinese goods, though the Mexico tariff was later paused for one month. The EV industry faces potential cost increases for components like batteries and semiconductors. Tesla's Q4 2024 results showed adjusted EPS of 73 cents (missing the 76-cent estimate) and $25.70 billion in revenue (missing the $27.26 billion estimate), with a 7% year-over-year decline in production.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 973, "out": 152}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43443587/stocks-trim-losses-on-mexico-tariff-delay-gold-extends-records-tesla-sinks-6-whats-driving-markets-monday", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T17:58:22", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-04", "summary": "Tesla shares declined 6% on Monday amid broader market volatility triggered by President Trump's announcement of tariffs on Mexico, Canada, and China. While the Mexico tariff was suspended for one month following a pledge to increase border security, concerns regarding trade relations with China and potential retaliation weighed on tech-sensitive stocks. Other Magnificent Seven members, including Apple and Nvidia, also saw declines of 4% and 3.8%, respectively.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 973, "out": 152}}
