{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43427786/chamath-palihapitiya-relocates-business-to-nevada-citing-delaware-judicial-activism-against-tesla-shareholders", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T09:00:09", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-03", "summary": "Venture capitalist Chamath Palihapitiya has moved the incorporation of his last four companies to Nevada, citing concerns over Delaware's 'judicial activism' against Tesla shareholders. This follows a broader trend of companies relocating from states like California and Delaware to business-friendly environments like Texas and Nevada.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1160, "out": 96}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/social-media/25/02/43427609/former-greek-finance-minister-yanis-varoufakis-says-tiktok-ban-exposes-techno-feudal-power-urges-social-media-portability", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T08:29:07", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-03", "summary": "Former Greek Finance Minister Yanis Varoufakis warns that the TikTok ban highlights the excessive power of tech platform owners, whom he calls 'techno-feudal lords.' He advocates for 'interoperability' regulations to allow users to transfer followers between platforms. Wedbush analyst Dan Ives estimates a potential TikTok joint venture could be worth up to $50 billion, with potential buyers including Microsoft, Oracle, and a consortium led by MrBeast. Meanwhile, Meta has invested over $2 billion in creator payments in 2024 to attract users to Instagram Reels.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 146}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/asia/25/02/43425710/nvidia-supplier-tsmcs-shares-plunge-over-6-in-taiwan-as-ai-selloff-intensifies-amid-deepseek-impact", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T03:26:35", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-03", "summary": "TSMC shares fell 6.6% to 1,070 New Taiwan dollars following a global AI stock selloff triggered by Chinese firm DeepSeek. DeepSeek claims its R1 model cost $5.6 million to develop, a figure Wedbush analyst Dan Ives dismissed as likely fictional compared to the $100 million-plus cost of OpenAI's GPT-4. Concerns have been raised by figures like Tesla CEO Elon Musk and Scale AI CEO Alexandr Wang regarding DeepSeek's potential use of U.S. technology and acquisition of advanced chips. The White House is investigating the company for national security risks.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 146}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43425232/gary-black-warns-teslas-18-export-volume-at-risk-amid-trump-tariffs-full-scale-retaliatory-trade-war-possible", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-03T01:43:22", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-03", "summary": "Investor Gary Black warns that Tesla's global export strategy is at risk due to rising trade tensions and high interest rates. President Trump's 25% tariffs on Canadian and Mexican imports, effective Feb. 1, could trigger a retaliatory trade war. Data from Troy Teslike shows Tesla exported 323,499 vehicles in 2024, or 18.1% of its 1.79 million total deliveries, with the Shanghai factory accounting for 246,910 of those exports. The Federal Reserve maintains interest rates between 4.25% and 4.5%, keeping borrowing costs high for consumers.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 146}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/02/43476925/buying-palantir-stock-today-is-like-buying-tesla-stock-10-years-ago-dan-ives-says-this-could-be-a-1-trillion-market-cap", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-04T20:30:22", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-05", "summary": "Wedbush analyst Dan Ives compares buying Palantir stock today to buying Tesla stock in 2015, suggesting Palantir could reach a $1 trillion market cap. Palantir reported its sixth consecutive quarter of beating analyst estimates, with 36% year-over-year revenue growth and 52% growth in the U.S. The company closed 129 deals worth over $1 million and 58 deals worth at least $5 million in the fourth quarter. Palantir shares rose 22.5% to $102.53 following the report.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 146}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/cryptocurrency/25/02/43473182/could-the-trump-established-sovereign-wealth-fund-invest-in-bitcoin-nvidia-tiktok", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-04T18:11:56", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-05", "summary": "President Trump's executive order to create a U.S. Sovereign Wealth Fund (SWF) has sparked debate over its structure and potential investments. Unlike a Bitcoin-only reserve, the SWF could include equities, bonds, real estate, and commodities. Experts suggest the fund might invest in technology companies like Nvidia and Tesla, or even acquire stakes in entities like TikTok for national security. Challenges include the U.S.'s status as a net debtor, with experts noting that deficit reduction, potentially via the DOGE initiative, is required to generate surplus capital for investment.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 960, "out": 146}}
