{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/02/43576866/tesla-researcher-says-ev-giant-is-skipping-a-step-to-driverless-operations-it-took-waymo-three-years", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-08T04:40:19", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-08", "summary": "Tesla researcher Troy Teslike criticized Tesla's approach to autonomy, arguing the company is skipping a necessary step before achieving fully driverless operations. Teslike cited Waymo's three-year transition (2017-2020) from supervised to driverless as a benchmark. Tesla CEO Elon Musk plans to begin testing autonomous ride-hailing in Austin, Texas, in June with FSD-equipped vehicles, aiming for multi-city operations by year-end.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 857, "out": 114}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43576469/tesla-launches-free-supercharging-offer-on-model-s-x-in-us-to-battle-drop-in-vehicle-deliveries", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-08T02:19:23", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-08", "summary": "Tesla is offering free Supercharging for the duration of ownership to customers who purchase or lease a new Model S or Model X in the U.S., Canada, Puerto Rico, Europe, and the Middle East. This follows a 11.5% year-over-year decline in January sales of China-made vehicles (63,238 units). Tesla also reported a 2024 global delivery total of 1.79 million vehicles, down from 1.81 million in 2023, and expects production of a refreshed Model Y to cause several weeks of lost output in Q1, with deliveries starting in March.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 857, "out": 114}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43581767/elon-musks-former-employees-warn-federal-workers-about-long-hours-firings-and-much-more", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-09T19:50:15", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "Elon Musk's management style, characterized by high expectations and rapid decision-making, is causing friction among federal workers as he takes on a role at the U.S. DOGE Service. The Washington Post reported that his approach, previously applied at Tesla, SpaceX, and Twitter, contrasts with the stability valued in the federal workforce. The report highlighted the firing of Twitter employee Eric Frohnhoefer as an example of Musk's leadership style.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 857, "out": 114}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43581013/lucids-record-deliveries-figure-ais-breakthrough-teslas-hiring-spree-and-more-this-week-in-mobility", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-09T15:00:49", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-09", "summary": "Tesla is hiring for Optimus robot production, with roles based primarily in California. Additionally, researcher Troy Teslike predicts Tesla will begin shipping Model Y vehicles from its Berlin gigafactory to Canada to avoid U.S. import tariffs. Other mobility news includes Lucid Group reporting a 51% increase in January deliveries and Figure AI announcing a breakthrough in its in-house robot AI.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 857, "out": 114}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/02/43580296/trumps-sovereign-wealth-fund-iran-sanctions-tariffs-musks-doge-target-and-tax-plans-top-economics-updates-this-week", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-09T11:00:42", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-09", "summary": "President Trump announced plans for a U.S. sovereign wealth fund. Meanwhile, economist Jason Furman analyzed Elon Musk's DOGE fiscal targets, estimating that Musk's proposed spending cuts would total approximately $1.5 trillion annually. Additionally, the Committee for a Responsible Federal Budget warned that Trump's proposed tax plan could reduce federal revenue by up to $11.2 trillion over the next decade.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 857, "out": 114}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/02/43580165/musks-government-role-trumps-tariffs-bukeles-prison-proposal-doge-scandal-and-chevrons-venezuela-business-this-week-in-politics", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-09T10:00:19", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-09", "summary": "Elon Musk has been appointed as a 'special government employee' to lead the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE). The initiative has faced scrutiny, including a legal dispute regarding staffer Marko Elez's access to Treasury Department data and his subsequent resignation. Separately, President Trump has imposed tariffs on Canada, China, and Mexico.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 857, "out": 114}}
