{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43608591/taiwan-semiconductors-trillion-dollar-valuation-the-chipmaker-enabling-ai-boom", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T21:15:48", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Taiwan Semiconductor (TSM) has seen its stock surge 256% over the last five years, reaching a trillion-dollar valuation by capitalizing on the AI boom. The company manufactures chips for major firms including Tesla, Nvidia, and Apple. TSM expects Q1 2025 revenue between $25 billion and $25.8 billion, despite impacts from a January 2025 earthquake. The company reported Q4 revenue of $26.88 billion, up 38.8%, with gross margins at 59%. TSM has committed $38 billion–$42 billion in fiscal 2025 capex and plans significant domestic expansion, including 1nm and 1.4nm fabs in Taiwan and continued production in the U.S. and Germany.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1424, "out": 158}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/analyst-ratings/25/02/43605835/where-tesla-stands-with-analysts", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T20:00:32", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Over the last three months, 36 analysts have provided ratings for Tesla (TSLA), with 7 bullish, 11 somewhat bullish, 11 indifferent, 1 somewhat bearish, and 6 bearish. The average 12-month price target is $362.72, ranging from a low of $24.86 to a high of $550.00. Tesla reported 2024 global deliveries of nearly 1.8 million vehicles. Financial metrics as of December 31, 2024, include a 2.15% revenue growth rate, a 9.0% net margin, a 3.24% return on equity, and a 1.91% return on assets. The company's debt-to-equity ratio is 0.19.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1424, "out": 158}}
