{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/02/43603073/mobileye-gains-analyst-upgrade-on-2025-catalysts-but-profit-delays-and-competition-keep-rating-neutral", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T18:23:08", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "BofA Securities upgraded Mobileye Global Inc (MBLY) from Underperform to Neutral and raised its price target from $12 to $19. Analyst John P. Babcock cited potential contract wins in 2025 as catalysts, though earnings growth is not expected to inflect positively until 2027. Babcock projects fiscal 2025 sales of $1.73 billion, 2026 sales of $1.81 billion, and 2027 sales of $2.07 billion. The report notes that Mobileye's projected annual robotaxi deployments by 2040 are expected to be less than one-fifth of Tesla's robotaxi volumes.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1424, "out": 158}}
