{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43588718/lucid-ceo-envisions-ev-maker-licensing-tech-more-than-building-cars", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T12:10:15", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "Lucid CEO Peter Rawlinson aims to shift his company's business model to 80% licensing and 20% car manufacturing, similar to an 'Intel inside' strategy. This mirrors Elon Musk's efforts to position Tesla as an AI and robotics company, including plans to license its Full Self-Driving technology to rivals, though automotive revenue still accounted for nearly 79% of Tesla's 2024 revenue.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1031, "out": 97}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43586493/jpmorgan-bofa-equifax-honda-block-and-many-more-may-get-relief-after-cfpb-dissolution-as-director-vought-halts-activities-maryland-senator-says-will-ensure-the-body-continues-to-fight-for-consumers", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T09:46:03", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) suspended operations after acting director Russell Vought halted investigations and supervisory activities, citing an 'excessive' $711.6 million balance. This follows Elon Musk's call to dissolve the agency. The suspension impacts ongoing enforcement actions against companies including Equifax, Honda, Block, Capital One, Walmart, Rocket Companies, and major banks like JPMorgan and Bank of America. While some tech leaders support the dissolution, Senator Chris Van Hollen stated the CFPB is protected by law and vowed to fight for its continuation.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1017, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43586484/google-deepmind-ceo-calls-deepseek-ai-best-work-from-china-but-says-hype-is-overblown-theres-no-actual-new-scientific-advance", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T09:44:41", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "Google DeepMind CEO Demis Hassabis praised DeepSeek's AI model as 'probably the best work' from China but stated it lacks significant new scientific advances, relying on known techniques. Hassabis questioned DeepSeek's low-cost claims and chip usage. While DeepSeek's launch fueled a surge in Chinese tech stocks, Hassabis and Alphabet CEO Sundar Pichai maintain that Google's Gemini models remain superior in efficiency and performance. Hassabis estimates AGI could be achieved within five years.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1017, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/cryptocurrency/25/02/43586218/bitcoin-advocate-balaji-pushes-end-the-fed-author-ron-paul-for-central-bank-chair-amid-elon-musks-support-nothing-can-stop-an-idea", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T09:13:24", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "Bitcoin advocate Balaji Srinivasan and Senator Mike Lee are advocating for Ron Paul to lead the Federal Reserve, a move supported by Elon Musk. The discussion centers on Paul's 'End the Fed' philosophy. While Musk previously expressed interest in having Paul join the proposed Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), Paul has indicated he does not seek an official position. The initiative aims for federal spending cuts, though experts project more modest savings than the targeted $2 trillion.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1017, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43585701/tesla-ceo-elon-musk-vp-of-finance-address-allegations-of-tax-fraud-losses-were-high-for-many-years-so-carry-forward", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T08:05:15", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk and VP of Finance Sendil Palani addressed tax fraud allegations on X, stating the company complies with global tax regulations. They explained that Tesla does not pay federal income tax due to net operating loss carry-forwards resulting from years of unprofitability. Tesla reported a 2024 net income of $7.09 billion and total revenue of $97.69 billion, with earnings per share of $2.04, down 53% from the previous year.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1017, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43585669/elon-musk-shuts-down-tiktok-buyout-rumors-says-he-prefers-to-build-companies-from-scratch-i-rarely-acquire-companies", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T07:55:32", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "Elon Musk has publicly dismissed rumors of a TikTok acquisition, stating he prefers to build companies from scratch and has not placed a bid. President Donald Trump recently signed an executive order delaying the enforcement of a ban on the app. While Trump previously expressed openness to a potential deal involving Musk or Oracle's Larry Ellison, China has reportedly taken a firm stance against a forced sale of TikTok's U.S. operations.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1017, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43583838/florida-engineer-says-his-tesla-cybertruck-crashed-into-a-light-post-when-fsd-was-deployed-it-is-easy-to-get-complacent-dont", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T05:55:50", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "A Florida software engineer reported that his Tesla Cybertruck crashed into a curb and a light post while using Full Self-Driving (FSD) version 13.2.4. The driver noted the vehicle failed to slow down or exit the lane. This incident follows an ongoing NHTSA investigation into 2.4 million Tesla vehicles regarding FSD performance in low-visibility conditions and concerns that Tesla's marketing may encourage driver complacency.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1017, "out": 119}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43583247/tesla-investor-ross-gerber-slams-fsd-on-cybertruck-as-not-usable-says-its-not-even-in-the-same-league-as-waymo", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-10T03:02:54", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-10", "summary": "Tesla investor Ross Gerber criticized Tesla's Full Self-Driving (FSD) version 13.2.6 on the Cybertruck, calling it 'not usable' and inferior to Waymo. While some users reported better experiences, researcher Troy Teslike questioned Tesla's development approach. Goldman Sachs analyst Mark Delaney maintains a Neutral rating and $345 price target, forecasting $115 million in robotaxi revenue by 2027. The NHTSA is currently investigating 2.6 million Tesla vehicles equipped with FSD.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1360, "out": 108}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/global/25/02/43636959/tesla-stock-is-tumbling-tuesday-whats-driving-the-action", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T19:34:10", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-12", "summary": "Tesla shares fell 5.60% to $331.17 on Tuesday after competitor BYD announced plans to make advanced smart driving a standard feature across its lineup, including in a vehicle priced under 70,000 yuan. BYD also announced an AI partnership with DeepSeek. Meanwhile, Tesla confirmed it remains on track to launch autonomous ride-hailing services in Austin in June, though FSD remains unapproved in China due to local restrictions.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1360, "out": 108}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43635839/lyft-rides-a-bullish-wave-ahead-of-q4-earnings-but-will-robotaxis-be-the-real-game-changer", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T18:54:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-12", "summary": "Lyft is set to report Q4 2024 earnings with analyst expectations of 22 cents per share and $1.56 billion in revenue. The company plans to deploy Mobileye-powered robotaxis in Dallas by 2026. JPMorgan analyst Samik Chatterjee noted the move as a competitive step against Uber and Tesla, though Lyft still lacks an original equipment manufacturer partner for its vehicles.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1360, "out": 108}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/economics/macro-economic-events/25/02/43635364/us-stocks-dip-as-powell-stays-cautious-intel-climbs-tesla-sinks-to-11-week-low", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T18:36:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-12", "summary": "Tesla shares dropped over 4% to an 11-week low on Tuesday, pressured by weak January auto sales in China. The broader U.S. market saw mixed results as Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell signaled no immediate interest rate cuts, while investors awaited January Consumer Price Index data.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1360, "out": 108}}
