{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43621302/justin-trudeau-slams-unacceptable-us-tariffs-after-trump-imposes-25-levy-on-metal-imports-canadians-will-stand-up-strongly-and-firmly-if-we-need-to", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T13:11:36", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau criticized new U.S. tariffs of 25% on steel and aluminum imports, effective March 4, as 'unacceptable.' The tariffs are expected to increase production costs for automotive companies including Tesla, Ford, and General Motors, with estimates suggesting a $2,000 price increase for new cars.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43620349/tesla-still-on-track-to-launch-autonomous-ride-hailing-in-austin-by-june-says-elon-musk", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T12:49:50", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk confirmed the company is on track to launch autonomous ride-hailing in Austin, Texas, in June using Model Y and Model 3 vehicles equipped with Full Self-Driving (FSD) technology. Musk also stated plans to expand the service to other American cities by the end of 2025. The dedicated Cybercab, which lacks steering wheels and pedals, is scheduled for production in 2026.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43619522/former-exec-sees-tesla-taking-over-uber-in-ride-hail-with-robotaxis-but-this-fund-manager-believes-elon-musks-ev-giant-wont-have-a-network-as-large", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T12:17:21", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Former Tesla executive Jorge Milburn argued that Tesla could dominate the ride-hailing market through a saturation strategy and lower costs compared to Uber. However, fund manager Gary Black countered that Uber's 170 million monthly active users provide a significant cost advantage that Tesla's smaller network may struggle to match. Uber is currently partnering with Waymo for autonomous rides in Atlanta.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43617724/deploying-tesla-superchargers-cost-40000-45000-per-stall-or-roughly-the-price-of-model-3-sedan-says-exec", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T11:13:23", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Tesla executive Max de Zegher stated that deploying a Supercharger stall currently costs between $40,000 and $45,000. The company aims to deploy its new V4 Superchargers with V4 cabinets for under $40,000 per stall, with pilot sites expected in Q3 2024. Tesla added over 11,000 stalls in 2024, bringing the global total to over 65,000.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43616177/tesla-exec-says-performance-variant-seven-seat-interior-on-new-model-y-will-launch-later-this-year", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T08:57:48", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Tesla VP of Vehicle Engineering Lars Moravy announced that the Performance variant of the refreshed Model Y will launch later in 2025. Production of the refreshed Model Y began recently across four global factories, with deliveries scheduled to start in March. Tesla reported 1.79 million global vehicle deliveries in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43615191/byds-gods-eye-and-huaweis-autonomous-driving-progress-spark-concerns-for-tesla-ross-gerber-points-out-all-use-lidar", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T07:17:29", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Industry experts and investors are questioning Tesla's vision-only approach to autonomous driving as competitors like BYD and Huawei integrate LIDAR technology. Ross Gerber noted that all major competitors use LIDAR, while Gary Black suggested autonomous driving is becoming commoditized. Tesla's FSD system is currently under investigation by the NHTSA.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43614807/byd-teams-up-with-deepseek-to-outpace-tesla-in-budget-friendly-ai-driven-tech-for-chinese-cars-amid-regulatory-roadblocks", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T06:35:17", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "BYD has launched its 'Eyes of God' driver-assistance system for budget vehicles, including a $9,600 hatchback, in partnership with DeepSeek. This move challenges Tesla in the Chinese market, where Tesla faces regulatory delays for its FSD software. While Tesla charges $8,000 plus a $99 monthly subscription for FSD in the U.S., BYD is integrating its system as a standard feature.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 866, "out": 103}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43614443/tesla-starts-production-at-shanghai-megafactory-in-less-than-9-months-of-beginning-construction", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T05:58:37", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Tesla has commenced production at its new Shanghai Megafactory less than nine months after construction began in May. The first Megapack, a battery unit capable of storing over 3.9 MWh, will be shipped to Australia. This facility is Tesla's first dedicated energy storage factory outside the U.S., complementing its Lathrop, California plant. Tesla's energy segment reported over $3 billion in Q4 revenue, with the company expecting at least 50% year-over-year growth in energy storage deployment for 2025.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 947, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/asia/25/02/43613949/tesla-supplier-catl-eyes-5-billion-hong-kong-listing-amid-us-sanctions-market-revival-report", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T04:21:06", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "Contemporary Amperex Technology Co. Ltd. (CATL), a major battery supplier to Tesla, is preparing to file for a secondary listing in Hong Kong that could raise at least $5 billion. This move follows U.S. authorities adding CATL to a list of companies allegedly working with China's military on Jan. 7. The listing would be one of Hong Kong's largest in three years, as the company seeks to diversify funding amidst U.S.-China tensions.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 947, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43613190/super-micro-computer-gamestop-mcdonalds-monday-com-and-tesla-why-these-stocks-are-on-investors-radars-today", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-11T02:03:31", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-11", "summary": "On Monday, Tesla shares fell 3.01% to close at $350.73, following CEO Elon Musk's response to tax fraud allegations. The stock's 52-week range is $138.80 to $488.54. Other notable market movements included Super Micro Computer rising 17.56%, GameStop climbing 9.66%, McDonald's increasing 4.80%, and Monday.com soaring 26.46%.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 947, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/trading-ideas/25/02/43678956/congress-member-josh-gottheimer-dumps-nvidia-microsoft-loads-up-on-tesla-stocks-instead", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-12T22:48:14", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-13", "summary": "U.S. Rep. Josh Gottheimer (D-N.J.) disclosed multiple stock transactions between Jan. 8 and Jan. 31, including selling Nvidia and Microsoft shares while purchasing Tesla stock in three transactions totaling $3,000 to $45,000. Gottheimer also bought Visa and Johnson & Johnson shares. The move into Tesla is noted for its potential connection to CEO Elon Musk's relationship with President Donald Trump.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 947, "out": 122}}
