{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/government/regulations/25/02/43724315/us-stocks-set-for-a-volatile-start-analyst-dismisses-chances-of-20-sp-500-gain-for-third-year-in-a-row-but-says-investors-should-be-optimistic", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-14T11:05:18", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-14", "summary": "U.S. stock futures were flat on Friday following Thursday's gains, where the Dow rose 0.77% and the Nasdaq gained 1.5% behind rallies in Nvidia and Tesla. January PPI rose 3.5% annually. Wells Fargo strategist Scott Wren expressed caution regarding a third consecutive year of 20%+ S&P 500 gains, projecting a 12% gain for the year. Investors are monitoring upcoming economic data, including retail sales and industrial production.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1101, "out": 120}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43721445/apple-tesla-and-other-mag-7-peers-too-expensive-top-hedge-fund-challenges-overvaluation-concerns-says-they-are-fairly-priced-if-they-sustain-20-earnings-growth-rate", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-14T07:01:02", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-14", "summary": "Bridgewater Associates' Karen Karniol-Tambour challenged concerns that 'Magnificent Seven' stocks, including Tesla, are overvalued. She argued that these companies are fairly priced if they sustain a 20% earnings growth rate, noting they only need 14% annual growth to justify their current premiums. This contrasts with other analysts, such as Adam Parker of Trivariate Research, who view the tech giants as overvalued and risky.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1101, "out": 120}}
