{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43754366/mark-zuckerberg-follows-elon-musks-footsteps-as-meta-reportedly-plans-major-investment-into-ai-powered-humanoid-robots", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-15T05:15:50", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-15", "summary": "Meta is reportedly planning a significant investment into AI-powered humanoid robots, forming a new team within its Reality Labs division led by former GM Cruise CEO Marc Whitten. Meta is discussing the initiative with robotics firms like Unitree Robotics and Figure AI. This follows Tesla's announced plans to produce thousands of Optimus humanoid robots for its factories, which Musk projects could generate over $10 trillion in long-term revenue.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 845, "out": 97}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43759759/apple-and-meta-in-race-to-develop-ai-powered-humanoid-robots", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-16T20:50:16", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Apple and Meta are reportedly developing AI-powered humanoid robots, potentially competing with Tesla's Optimus. Meta has established a new unit within its Reality Labs division to develop software platforms for humanoid technology. Apple is exploring humanoid robotics through its advanced AI research teams. Google's DeepMind is also investigating robotics technology.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 845, "out": 97}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/entertainment/25/02/43759529/sheryl-crow-ditches-tesla-over-elon-musks-doge-and-trump-ties", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-16T18:45:16", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Musician Sheryl Crow announced she is parting ways with her Tesla vehicle, citing disapproval of CEO Elon Musk's political ties and his role leading the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) under the Trump administration.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 845, "out": 97}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43759231/trumps-auto-tariffs-teslas-stock-plunge-ubers-tesla-partnership-musks-dubai-loop-and-starbase-city", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-16T16:00:22", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Tesla shares have dropped over 25% from their December peak, with analyst Mark Newton predicting a potential further 12% decline in the next one to two weeks. Meanwhile, Uber CEO Dara Khosrowshahi expressed interest in a partnership to deploy Tesla's autonomous vehicles on Uber's platform. Additionally, President Donald Trump has hinted at potential auto tariffs starting April 2, and Elon Musk's Boring Company plans to build a 'Dubai Loop' capable of transporting 20,000 passengers per hour.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1137, "out": 128}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43758282/musks-doge-under-treasury-scrutiny-trumps-tariffs-impacting-soda-industry-and-more", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-16T10:00:42", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-16", "summary": "The Treasury Department is auditing security controls for federal payment systems following concerns regarding access granted to Elon Musk's Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE). Separately, President Donald Trump has nominated Jonathan Morrison, an Apple employee and former NHTSA chief counsel, to lead the U.S. auto safety regulator, which oversees Tesla. Additionally, short-seller Jim Chanos has questioned a potential $400 million, five-year government contract for Tesla's armored Cybertrucks.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1137, "out": 128}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43770024/from-tech-to-politics-how-elon-musk-is-empowering-far-right-across-the-globe", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-17T21:20:16", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "A report indicates that Elon Musk is supporting right-wing political movements and policies in at least 18 countries, focusing on reducing immigration and curbing business regulation. Musk has used his platform X to engage with political figures and protests globally, including in Brazil, Ireland, India, and Turkey. While some right-wing politicians benefit from his association, leaders like French President Emmanuel Macron have criticized his influence, and political scientists note the growing power of tech billionaires in shaping global politics.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1137, "out": 128}}
