{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43765071/teslas-california-sales-hit-four-year-low-amid-political-concerns-researcher-says-left-leaning-customers-are-turning-away-from-ev-giant", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-17T12:28:51", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Tesla's California sales dropped to 26.1% of its total U.S. sales in Q4 2024, the lowest level in four years, down from 27.9% in Q4 2023. Researcher Troy Teslike suggests this decline may be linked to CEO Elon Musk's political actions. This trend aligns with broader challenges, including a 12% drop in California sales for 2024 and a 13% decline in European registrations, contributing to Tesla's first annual delivery decline.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1137, "out": 128}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43764223/elon-musk-points-to-bill-clinton-era-government-job-cuts-amid-tesla-showroom-protests", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-17T10:44:37", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Elon Musk referenced the Bill Clinton-era reduction of the federal workforce to defend current downsizing efforts amid protests at Tesla showrooms in New York, Seattle, and California. The controversy has impacted the brand, with Ross Gerber planning to sell his Cybertruck due to public hostility. Additionally, Tesla's German sales reportedly fell 60% year-over-year in January. Tesla shares closed at $355.84 on Friday, marking a 14.01% decline over the past month.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1137, "out": 128}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43762639/tesla-rival-sets-2027-target-for-the-mass-production-of-all-solid-state-batteries-will-be-mainly-used-in-high-end-models", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-17T07:09:25", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "BYD plans to start demonstration use of all-solid-state batteries by 2027, with broader adoption after 2030. The company has been developing this technology since 2013 and is currently conducting trial production of cells with 20 Ah and 60 Ah capacities. BYD CTO Sun Huajun noted that sulfide electrolytes are being used, and while costs are currently high due to low volume, they are expected to become comparable to liquid ternary batteries as adoption grows. These batteries are intended primarily for high-end vehicle models.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 879, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/general/market-summary/25/02/43762416/billionaire-ray-dalios-bridgewater-trims-holdings-in-6-of-magnificent-7-stocks-amid-valuation-concerns-adds-this-automotive-stock-after-3-years", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-17T06:24:09", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Ray Dalio's Bridgewater Associates trimmed its holdings in six 'Magnificent 7' stocks during Q4 2024, including Apple (-40%), Amazon (-35%), Nvidia (-26%), Microsoft (-23%), Meta (-23%), and Alphabet (-17%). Conversely, the fund added 153,589 shares of Tesla, valued at $62.025 million, marking its first position in the company since Q4 2021. Dalio expressed concerns regarding high valuations of tech stocks, emphasizing a preference for value and productivity-driven investments.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 879, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/global/25/02/43762315/ai-adoption-to-boost-chinese-stocks-by-up-to-200-billion-predicts-goldman-sachs-eps-to-rise-by-2-5-annually-over-next-10-years", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-17T06:10:00", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Goldman Sachs raised its MSCI China Index target from 75 to 85, forecasting a 16% upside and potential $200 billion inflow into Chinese stocks over the next 12 months. Analysts predict AI adoption, including models like DeepSeek, could boost Chinese companies' EPS by 2.5% annually over the next decade. The report contrasts the valuation of the 'Magnificent Seven' (average P/E of 41.4) with the Hang Seng Tech Index (average P/E of 20.5).", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 879, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43761581/ross-gerber-says-hes-eventually-selling-his-cybertruck-because-the-hate-is-real-as-protests-rock-tesla-showrooms", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-17T03:14:08", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-17", "summary": "Ross Gerber, CEO of Gerber Kawasaki, announced plans to sell his Cybertruck due to public hostility toward the Tesla brand. This follows protests at Tesla showrooms in cities like New York and Seattle regarding Elon Musk's role in the Department of Government Efficiency. Additionally, singer Sheryl Crow documented selling her Tesla, and reports indicate a 60% year-over-year drop in German Tesla sales in January. Tesla shares fell 14.01% over the past month.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 879, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/trading-ideas/long-ideas/25/02/43795095/viking-bails-on-apple-tesla-and-trims-nvidia-is-this-a-big-tech-rethink", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T20:02:30", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Viking Global Investors exited its entire positions in Apple (4.86 million shares) and Tesla (over 436,000 shares) during Q4 2024. The firm also trimmed its Nvidia holdings by 10.3%. The move reflects a broader sector shift, with Viking reducing its Information Technology exposure from 19.06% to 17.96% while increasing its Financials allocation from 25.58% to 28.45%.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 879, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43781034/bill-gates-hopes-elon-musk-will-rethink-slashing-usaid-their-work-is-something-every-taxpayer-would-be-proud-of", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T13:45:41", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Microsoft co-founder Bill Gates expressed optimism in an interview that Elon Musk will reconsider his plans to slash USAID programs. Musk, who leads the Department of Government Efficiency, has publicly criticized USAID as wasteful. Gates defended the agency's work in famine relief and HIV medication distribution, stating it is something taxpayers should be proud of.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 879, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43780644/sam-altmans-openai-reportedly-considers-special-voting-rights-to-thwart-elon-musks-acquisition-attempt-and-defend-future-unsolicited-bids", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T13:39:34", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "OpenAI is considering granting special voting rights to its non-profit board to defend against unsolicited takeover bids, including a recent $97.4 billion offer from Elon Musk which the board rejected. Analysts at Oppenheimer suggested that Musk's acquisition attempt serves as a diversion from his leadership at Tesla. The proposed governance changes would allow the board to overrule major investors like Microsoft and SoftBank.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 879, "out": 122}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/legal/25/02/43778605/tesla-files-fresh-lawsuit-against-matthews-after-court-defeat", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T12:49:12", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "On February 14, 2025, a U.S. District Court Judge denied Tesla's request for a temporary restraining order against Matthews International regarding its dry battery electrode (DBE) technology. This follows an early February 2025 arbitration win for Matthews. Tesla subsequently filed a new lawsuit in the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of California. Matthews, which holds U.S. Patent No. 12,136,727, claims the lawsuit is meritless. Matthews has been a supplier to Tesla since 2019.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43775516/after-discounts-tesla-is-now-offering-free-vinyl-wraps-to-boost-foundation-series-cybertruck-sales", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T10:53:58", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Tesla is offering free XPEL colored vinyl wraps for Foundation Series Cybertruck buyers who take delivery by March 31, 2025. The Foundation Series, a limited edition with laser-etched badges, starts at $99,990, while the regular Cybertruck starts at $79,990. Tesla is also offering discounts of up to $6,000 on the Foundation Series to clear inventory.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/analyst-ratings/analyst-color/25/02/43774671/tesla-bull-advises-ev-giant-investors-to-limit-emotion-tied-to-the-product-i-love-starbucks-but-i-wouldnt-own-sbux-stock", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T09:32:41", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Fund manager Gary Black advised Tesla investors to analyze the stock objectively rather than emotionally. He warned against relying on management's production forecasts instead of demand. Black remains optimistic about Tesla, citing the potential for a new, cheaper hatchback model priced between $25,000 and $30,000 to expand the company's total addressable market, provided it features a new form factor.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/25/02/43774570/elon-musk-sparks-debate-on-social-security-data-after-report-finds-millions-of-alive-centenarians-in-america", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T09:14:04", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Tesla CEO Elon Musk, serving on the Department of Government Efficiency, highlighted statistics showing millions of Americans over 100 years old listed as alive in Social Security Administration (SSA) records. A July 2023 SSA Inspector General audit identified 18.9 million number holders born before 1920 without death information, though 98% receive no payments. The SSA attributes this to pre-electronic record-keeping and notes that updating these records would cost $5-10 million.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43774256/gop-megadonor-ken-griffins-citadel-earns-77-return-from-palantir-despite-slashing-13-in-q4-adds-4-mag-7-while-cutting-stake-in-3", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T08:53:51", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "In Q4 2024, Citadel Advisors slashed its stake in Tesla by 86%, leaving a position valued at $82.465 million. The fund also reduced its holdings in Nvidia by 56% and Microsoft by 25%, while increasing stakes in Alphabet, Apple, Meta, and Amazon. Citadel also cut its Palantir holdings by 13%.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43774239/teslas-self-driving-ambitions-in-china-at-risk-as-us-china-trade-war-heats-up-its-a-bit-of-a-quandary-says-elon-musk", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T08:49:00", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Tesla faces delays in obtaining approval for its autonomous driving technology in China, reportedly due to U.S.-China trade tensions. CEO Elon Musk noted challenges regarding data transfer restrictions between the two nations. Tesla is currently training its system using publicly available videos and simulations, with a goal of achieving unsupervised self-driving in China by the end of 2026. Meanwhile, production of the refreshed Model Y has begun at the Shanghai Gigafactory.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43774109/elon-musks-india-plans-back-on-track-tesla-lists-jobs-after-meeting-with-prime-minister-modi", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T08:39:56", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Tesla has listed 13 job openings in Mumbai and Delhi, India, covering roles in vehicle service, sales, customer support, and operations. This follows a meeting between CEO Elon Musk and Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Previous expansion plans were hindered by high import duties.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43773352/stanley-druckenmiller-ditches-broadcom-ups-ante-on-big-tech", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T07:17:10", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "In Q4 2024, Stanley Druckenmiller's Duquesne Family Office exited its entire stake in Broadcom and reduced its tech portfolio by selling shares in Microsoft, Adobe, and Autodesk. Conversely, the firm initiated new positions in Tesla, Amazon, and Alphabet. Tesla's stock has surged over 83% in the past year but declined more than 16% over the last month.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 797, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43772576/tesla-to-start-delivering-shanghai-made-refreshed-model-ys-next-week", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T05:36:44", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Tesla has commenced production of the refreshed Model Y at its Shanghai Gigafactory, with deliveries expected to start in late February or next week. The rear-wheel drive variant is priced at 263,500 yuan, while the long-range all-wheel drive variant starts at 303,500 yuan. Tesla reported 1.79 million global vehicle deliveries in 2024, down from 1.81 million in 2023.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1194, "out": 106}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/media/25/02/43771979/elon-musk-will-unleash-grok-3-tonight-tesla-integration-live-voice-mode-and-more-heres-what-to-expect", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-18T02:45:27", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-18", "summary": "Elon Musk's xAI is scheduled to launch Grok 3 in a live demo on February 17, 2025, at 8 p.m. PT. The update is expected to feature deep integration with Tesla vehicles for voice command interaction, along with self-correcting AI capabilities and a new live-voice mode. xAI reached a $50 billion valuation in November 2024.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1194, "out": 106}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/trading-ideas/25/02/43827658/exclusive-apple-nvidia-tesla-or-boeing-which-company-faces-the-biggest-risk-from-trumps-china-tariffs-35-say-this-stock", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T19:58:19", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "A Benzinga poll conducted February 11-12, 2025, found that 35% of respondents view Apple as most at risk from Donald Trump's China tariffs, while Tesla and Nvidia tied for second place at 28%. Additionally, 54% of respondents believe these tariffs will hurt U.S. businesses and consumers.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1194, "out": 106}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/options/25/02/43819730/10-consumer-discretionary-stocks-whale-activity-in-todays-session", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T17:35:17", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Options activity for Tesla (TSLA) shows a bullish call option sweep expiring February 21, 2025, with a $370.00 strike price. The trade involved 221 contracts at a total cost of $80.6K, with 103,841 contracts traded today.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1194, "out": 106}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43818555/trade-war-redux-a-bumpy-ride-ahead-for-these-etfs-after-trumps-tariff-move-on-auto-pharma-chip-imports", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T16:59:00", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "President Donald Trump plans to impose a 25% tariff on auto, semiconductor, and pharmaceutical imports, with auto tariffs expected to take effect April 2, 2025. ETFs such as the Global X Autonomous & Electric Vehicles ETF (DRIV) and First Trust NASDAQ Global Auto Index Fund (CARZ) are noted for their exposure to Tesla and other automakers, potentially facing volatility due to these trade policies.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1194, "out": 106}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/insights/options/25/02/43817114/teslas-options-frenzy-what-you-need-to-know", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T16:15:44", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Analysis of 488 unusual Tesla (TSLA) options trades shows 47% bullish sentiment and 36% bearish. Investors are targeting a price range between $250.0 and $720.0 over the next three months. Tesla's stock is currently trading at $360.64, up 1.84%, with earnings expected in 62 days.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1194, "out": 106}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43808480/teslas-india-launch-will-not-help-prevent-drop-in-global-deliveries-in-2025-says-researcher", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T11:46:34", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Researcher Troy Teslike predicts 2025 will be another down year for Tesla, with global deliveries expected to be 1% lower than the 1.79 million vehicles delivered in 2024. Teslike also forecasts Q1 2025 deliveries will fall below 400,000 units. While Tesla CEO Elon Musk previously targeted 20-30% delivery growth for 2025, the company later stated it expects to return to growth without reiterating specific targets. Tesla plans to start production of new, more affordable vehicles in the first half of 2025 and is hiring in India, though Teslike views India as a tiny market for Tesla's price range.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 824, "out": 136}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43808344/elon-musks-x-seeks-44-billion-valuation-in-new-funding-round-amid-renewed-investor-interest", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T11:44:28", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Elon Musk's social media company, X, is reportedly in discussions to secure funding at a $44 billion valuation. This follows a period of devaluation, including a Fidelity assessment that valued X Holdings at $12.3 billion, which was 72% below the initial acquisition price. Investor sentiment has reportedly improved due to Musk's position in the Trump administration and a return of major advertisers like Amazon and Apple. Additionally, Morgan Stanley recently completed the sale of $3 billion in X debt.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 824, "out": 136}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43808316/about-the-scarce-on-detail-tesla-robovan-meant-to-accomodate-big-families-including-elon-musks", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T11:39:56", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Elon Musk recently referenced the Tesla Robovan, a vehicle designed to transport up to 20 people or cargo, noting it is being built to accommodate his children. Unveiled in October alongside the two-seater Cybercab, the Robovan features an automatic load-leveling suspension and lacks side mirrors or pedals. While the Cybercab is slated for 2026 production at under $30,000, no production timeline was provided for the Robovan. Tesla also plans to start production of new, more affordable models and the second-generation Roadster in 2025.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 824, "out": 136}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43806974/baidus-robotaxi-service-hits-1-1-million-paid-rides-in-q4-expands-to-hong-kong-as-1st-operator-allowed-to-test-autonomous-vehicles", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T09:46:30", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Baidu's robotaxi service, Apollo Go, achieved 1.1 million paid rides in Q4 2024, a 36% year-over-year increase, with 9 million cumulative rides. The service has transitioned to 100% driverless operations and received a permit to test in Hong Kong in November, marking its first expansion into a left-hand traffic market. Baidu utilizes its sixth-generation RT6 autonomous vehicle and is pursuing an asset-light scaling strategy to compete with rivals like Tesla and Waymo.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 824, "out": 136}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43806874/doge-fires-fda-staff-reviewing-musks-neuralink-we-should-be-worried-about-the-whole-trial", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T09:30:14", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Approximately 20 FDA employees from the Office of Neurological and Physical Medicine Devices, including some overseeing Elon Musk's Neuralink, were dismissed as part of a federal workforce purge. While sources suggest the employees were not specifically targeted for their work on Neuralink, experts warn the cuts could slow down the processing of medical device applications. Neuralink, which has secured over $600 million in funding, previously faced FDA inspection issues regarding animal experiment record-keeping in March.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 824, "out": 136}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43806303/tesla-rival-rivians-6-6-billion-federal-loan-under-scrutiny-as-trump-administration-reviews-funding", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T08:16:00", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Rivian's $6.6 billion federal loan for a planned Georgia manufacturing plant is under review by the Trump administration. The facility, intended to produce the R2 and R3 electric vehicles, aims for an annual capacity of 400,000 units with production starting by the end of 2028. The loan, structured in two phases of $3.4 billion and $2.6 billion, was finalized at the end of the Biden administration. Rivian maintains its commitment to the project, which is expected to create 7,500 permanent jobs.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 824, "out": 136}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43806208/elon-musks-doge-reports-nearly-47t-untraceable-in-federal-payments-makes-tas-tag-mandatory", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T08:00:07", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "The Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), led by Elon Musk, has made the Treasury Access Symbol (TAS) a mandatory field for federal payments to improve traceability. Previously, the field was optional, leaving approximately $4.7 trillion in payments difficult to track. This initiative is part of a broader effort to reduce federal waste, which has also included demands for data from the Social Security Administration and proposals to eliminate paper checks at the Treasury to save an estimated $750 million annually.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 824, "out": 136}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43805852/trump-shakes-global-trade-with-25-auto-chip-and-pharma-tariffs-announcement-asian-stocks-pare-their-five-day-rally", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T07:22:52", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "President Donald Trump announced plans for a 25% tariff on auto imports, potentially effective April 2. Sectoral tariffs on pharmaceuticals and semiconductor chips are also planned at 25% or higher. The announcement caused Asian stocks to retreat, particularly Japanese automakers. Tesla's Chinese rivals NIO, Li Auto, and BYD saw mixed results.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1018, "out": 88}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43805662/tesla-cybertruck-receives-5-star-safety-rating-apocalypse-level-safe-says-elon-musk", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T07:09:57", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "The NHTSA awarded the Tesla Cybertruck a 5-star overall safety rating, which applies to both 2024 and 2025 models. CEO Elon Musk described the vehicle as 'apocalypse-level safe,' noting it has the lowest overall injury probability and rollover risk of any pickup truck tested by the agency.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1018, "out": 88}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43805175/elon-musks-tesla-prepares-for-india-expansion-engineer-confirms-hiring-push-we-are-looking-for-motivated-talent-to-help-us", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-19T05:45:06", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-19", "summary": "Tesla is preparing to launch in India, as confirmed by employee Manish Bansal. The company has listed 14 job openings in cities including Delhi, Mumbai, and Pune, covering roles in service, sales, and operations. This follows previous interest from CEO Elon Musk and a meeting with Prime Minister Narendra Modi.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1018, "out": 88}}
