{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43846851/jeff-bezos-ex-wife-mackenzie-scotts-19b-donations-are-transforming-2000-nonprofits-report", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T13:23:41", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "MacKenzie Scott has donated over $19 billion to more than 2,000 nonprofits since 2019 through Yield Giving, with gifts averaging $5 million. Tesla co-founder Elon Musk previously labeled these donations 'Concerning.' Meanwhile, Jeff Bezos and Lauren Sánchez have engaged in significant philanthropy, though Bezos' Earth Fund recently withdrew support from a climate initiative.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 827, "out": 111}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/trading-ideas/long-ideas/25/02/43845840/controversy-and-opportunity-provide-fuel-for-direxions-tesla-bull-and-bear-funds", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T13:00:16", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Tesla remains a leading EV brand, with 2024 sales of 372,613 Model Y and 189,903 Model 3 units, while the Cybertruck sold 38,965 units. However, Tesla's brand value dropped 26% to $43 billion in 2025, and the stock fell 15% over the last month. Direxion offers leveraged ETFs: the bull fund TSLL (up 115% over the past year) and the bear fund TSLS (down 63% over 52 weeks).", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 827, "out": 111}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43844358/tesla-exec-pins-delay-in-cybertruck-crash-test-report-on-nhtsa-says-weve-known-it-was-5-star-from-the-beginning", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T12:16:36", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Tesla executive Lars Moravy stated that the delay in receiving a crash protection rating for the Cybertruck was due to the NHTSA's schedule. The vehicle, which began deliveries in November 2023, was recently awarded a 5-star safety rating by the NHTSA, which noted it has the lowest overall probability of injury and rollover risk of any pickup truck tested.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 827, "out": 111}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43842890/osha-cites-tesla-over-death-of-electrician-report", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T11:22:22", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "OSHA has cited Tesla for workplace safety violations following the August 1 electrocution death of contractor Victor Gomez Sr. at the Giga Texas factory. The factory, which produces the Model Y and Cybertruck with an annual capacity of over 375,000 vehicles, was also fined $7,000 for two safety violations in 2024.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 827, "out": 111}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/cryptocurrency/25/02/43842547/bitcoin-friendly-bank-stock-held-by-warren-buffett-and-cathie-wood-has-crushed-their-top-holdings-apple-and-tesla-in-2025", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T11:10:19", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Nu Holdings, a Brazil-based fintech firm, has gained 30.12% year-to-date in 2025, outperforming major holdings of Warren Buffett and Cathie Wood. Berkshire Hathaway holds 40.18 million shares of Nu, while Ark Invest holds 2.086 million. In contrast, Berkshire's top holding, Apple, is down 2.22%, and Ark's top holding, Tesla, is down 10.72% year-to-date.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 827, "out": 111}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43840909/trumps-goal-is-to-abolish-irs-and-let-all-the-outsiders-pay-says-newly-confirmed-commerce-secretary-howard-lutnick", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T08:56:09", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick confirmed the Trump administration's goal to abolish the IRS. Elon Musk, leading the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), aims to cut $1 trillion in spending. A recent Benzinga poll indicated that 35% of respondents believe Apple would bear the most impact from potential tariffs, compared to Tesla, Nvidia, and Boeing.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 827, "out": 111}}
