{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43838678/tesla-to-try-virtual-queue-system-at-select-superchargers-in-q2", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T05:18:33", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Tesla announced it will pilot a virtual queuing system at select Supercharger sites in Q2 to reduce wait times. If feedback is positive, the system will see a wider rollout later this year. Tesla continues to expand its network by over 20% year-over-year, with 65,495 connectors as of the end of 2024, up 19% from 54,892 at the end of 2023. The company is also working to add 500-1000 stalls monthly in North America.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1154, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43837935/palantir-plunges-as-alex-karp-plans-123-billion-stock-sale-jim-cramer-urges-palanteers-to-support-the-stock-right-now-as-pentagon-eyes-defense-cuts", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-20T03:39:59", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-20", "summary": "Palantir shares fell over 5% after CEO Alex Karp adopted a new Rule 10b5-1 trading plan to sell up to 9.98 million shares by September 12, potentially worth $1.23 billion. The stock decline also followed reports of potential 8% annual Pentagon budget cuts over five years. Palantir reported Q4 2024 revenue of $828 million and adjusted earnings of 14 cents per share.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1154, "out": 110}}
