{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43878703/institutional-investors-load-up-on-technology-and-financial-stocks-in-q4-while-reducing-positions-in-healthcare-sector-amid-political-uncertainty", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-21T12:45:36", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-21", "summary": "Institutional investors increased holdings in technology and financials during Q4 2024, while reducing exposure to the healthcare sector. Hedge funds specifically increased market value in Amazon, Nvidia, and Tesla, while reducing positions in Microsoft, Palantir, and PDD Holdings.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 1154, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43878167/elon-musks-tesla-recalls-nearly-380000-model-3-y-vehicles-in-us-over-loss-of-power-steering-assist-concerns", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-21T12:08:00", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-21", "summary": "Tesla is recalling 376,241 U.S. vehicles, specifically certain 2023 Model 3 and Model Y units, due to potential loss of power steering assist. Tesla has released an over-the-air software update to address the issue. While the company reports no known collisions or injuries, it identified over 3,000 related warranty claims. This follows a NHTSA probe into steering control complaints.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 847, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/government/regulations/25/02/43875557/donald-trump-airs-fort-knox-inspection-as-gold-edges-closer-to-3000-it-is-an-essential-component-of-portfolio-says-expert", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-21T08:23:33", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-21", "summary": "Gold is nearing $3,000 per ounce, with experts citing fiscal dominance as a factor in its recent performance. During the 2025 Conservative Political Action Conference, Tesla CEO Elon Musk and President Donald Trump discussed the public's right to inspect the gold at Fort Knox. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent noted that annual audits confirm the gold is accounted for.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 847, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/equities/25/02/43874865/nvidia-unveils-signs-ai-platform-for-teaching-american-sign-language-expanding-into-assistive-tech", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-21T06:56:46", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-21", "summary": "Nvidia unveiled 'Signs,' an AI-powered platform for American Sign Language learning, featuring a 3D avatar and real-time feedback. The platform aims to build a dataset of 400,000 video clips. While Nvidia focuses on this assistive tech, Tesla CEO Elon Musk's Neuralink is developing 'Blindsight' to restore vision. Nvidia's dataset will be public later this year, with demonstrations at the GTC conference, March 17-21.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 847, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43872450/alibaba-rivian-nu-holdings-walmart-and-tesla-why-these-5-stocks-are-on-investors-radars-today", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-21T01:33:07", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-21", "summary": "On February 20, 2025, Tesla stock fell 1.71% to close at $354.40, with a 52-week range of $138.80 to $488.54. Executive Lars Moravy stated via X that Cybertruck safety rating delays are due to the NHTSA's schedule. Other trending stocks included Alibaba, Rivian, Nu Holdings, and Walmart, all of which saw significant market movement following their respective financial reports.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 847, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/25/02/43901443/former-tesla-booster-now-warns-stock-faces-major-pain-in-2025", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-22T20:45:19", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-23", "summary": "Ross Gerber, CEO of Gerber Kawasaki and a Tesla shareholder, predicts a 50% decline in Tesla's stock price in 2025. Gerber cites concerns over Elon Musk's focus on AI over Tesla's core business, the feasibility of the June autonomous taxi rollout in Austin, reliance on camera-based self-driving, and potential brand damage from Musk's political ties. JPMorgan has set a $135 price target for Tesla.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 847, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/02/43900342/uber-ceo-reveals-elon-musks-stance-on-tesla-robotaxis-partnership-they-want-to-build-it-alone", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-22T08:07:40", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-22", "summary": "Uber CEO Dara Khosrowshahi stated that Elon Musk intends to launch Tesla's robotaxi service independently without integrating into Uber's platform. Consequently, Uber will compete with Tesla and Waymo in Austin. Uber previously exited in-house self-driving development in 2020 and is currently partnering with Waymo for autonomous rides in Austin and Atlanta.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 847, "out": 110}}
{"article_id": "https://www.benzinga.com/tech/25/02/43902958/rivians-new-edition-spacex-delays-teslas-decline-and-nikolas-bankruptcy-this-week-in-mobility", "symbol": "TSLA", "source_datetime_utc": "2025-02-23T15:00:19", "effective_trading_date": "2025-02-23", "summary": "Recent mobility sector news includes Rivian's new 'California Dune' R1 edition and its Q4 financial results, which showed a gross profit driven by regulatory credits rather than cost-cutting. Tesla experienced a four-year low in California sales. Additionally, SpaceX CEO Elon Musk alleged political delays in returning astronauts from the ISS, and Nikola Corp. filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy.", "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-lite", "tokens": {"in": 847, "out": 110}}
